title: cinnamon sugar pull apart loaf
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 8 x 4-inch loaf pan (do not use a dark coated pan).
In a small shallow bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon, blending well.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits, cutting each into 1/4 squares.
Dip each quarter into melted margarine; roll in sugar cinnamon mixture.
Arrange in greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes.
Loosen edges; remove from pan.
Serve warm on serving plate.

title: easy baked tomato
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sprinkle each tomato half with 1/2 teaspoon basil, some minced parsley and some wheat germ. Bake about 10 minutes. Makes 2 servings.

title: cereal christmas trees and wreaths
directions: Have all ingredients ready.
In a large saucepan, heat the butter and marshmallows over low heat, stirring until melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in the vanilla and food coloring.
Stir in the cereal until well coated.

title: pol's apple cake(opal t.)
directions: This cake is not only delicious, it's easy to make.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan and preheat the oven to 350°.
Blend eggs, oil and sugar until creamy; add flour a little at a time.
Blend well; batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples, coconut and nuts. Pour into tube pan and bake for 1 hour.
Remove from pan after about 30 minutes.
Top the warm cake with the following mixture.

title: giant soap bubbles
directions: You will need a wire coat hanger, bent into a loop.

title: coconut walnut bars
directions: Work together and pat in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle bottom with the coconut, then the chopped pecans; set aside.
Mix the box of German chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Pour over the coconut and pecans.
Mix the cream cheese and butter.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Dot all of this over the cake mixture at different spots.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes only.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Quarter the biscuits and roll each piece in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Layer in greased and floured tube pan.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; heat until sugar melts.
Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Invert onto serving plate.

title: 7 layer pea salad
directions: Place ingredients as listed in a 9 x 15-inch dish.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle with sugar, cheese and bacon.
Do not toss.
A great salad for family or church gathering.
I usually double everything except lettuce.
Chill 6 to 8 hours.

title: pepperoni squares
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 4 squares.
Press perforations to form a solid square.
(Each square is formed by 2 triangles.)
Cut each square into 4 smaller squares.
You will have 16 squares.
On each square, place 2 to 3 slices pepperoni, a few roasted peppers and Mozzarella cheese.
Fold the four corners to the center to form a diamond shape.
Bake according to the directions on the crescent rolls.
Can be made ahead of time and frozen.
Thaw and heat until warm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and onions; add egg and gradually beat in milk or water.
Drop from spoon into hot grease (safflower oil) until golden brown.
Makes 16.

title: artichoke sauce and spaghetti
directions: Drain artichokes and keep liquid. Quarter artichokes.
Saute mushrooms in skillet in the liquid. Add artichokes and remaining ingredients, except spaghetti. Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Serve over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: ham diet delight
directions: Cook onion and peppers until tender in 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add mushrooms, ham, gravy, wine and black pepper and heat.
Cook broken spaghetti in salted boiling water until just tender.
Cook asparagus spears until just tender.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon and drain, breaking into pieces.
Layer all ingredients.
Add dressing:
mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice. Toss right before serving time.
This can be made the day before and refrigerated overnight.

title: bacon
directions: Put it in a pan and flips it over.
Cooks until it's done. Then you can eat it.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from bone and cut into pieces.
Cook onions in a small amount of oil until tender, draining off excess oil.
Combine onions, green chilies, soups and sour cream.
Layer Doritos in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour soup mixture over chips.
Layer again and top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until cheese is melted and mixture is heated throughout.

title: blender chocolate mousse
directions: Blend like crazy until chocolate is melted.
Pour into 4 or 5 demitasse cups.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix ground beef with crackers, salt and pepper.
Add milk and mix well.
Spread mixture out (approximately 1/2-inch thick) on a rimmed cookie sheet.
Chill thoroughly and when firm, cut into squares.
Flour each square and brown in shortening.
Put in baking dish or leave in electric skillet.
Dilute soup with milk.
Pour over squares and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or simmer in skillet for 30 minutes.

title: mother's herb rice(1942)
directions: Put rice, onions, butter and broth in cooking dish or pan.
Mix all spices (herbs) together and sprinkle on top of rice and broth. Cover and cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not stir while cooking.

title: baked crabmeat and shrimp
directions: Chop up green pepper, onion and celery.
Slice mushrooms. Combine with shrimp, crabmeat, mayonnaise and seasonings in casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cow patties
directions: Peel and mash 3 ripe avocados, mix with 2 tsp lemon juice 1/4 tsp salt, set aside. Combine 1 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1 pkg. taco seasoning, mix well.
Set aside.

title: oyster cracker party food
directions: Mix dressing, oil and dill; add crackers and stir well. Refrigerate in tight container.
Will keep for weeks.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and 2 cups of sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, vanilla and sugar.
Add sugar to peanut butter mixture, a little at a time.
If it becomes too stiff, add 1 tablespoon of butter.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into this mixture using a toothpick.
Be sure to leave the eye.

title: tofu dip(dairyless dip)
directions: Process lemon and garlic in blender.
Add everything except parsley; add parsley last.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and spread in pizza pan.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes until golden; cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Slice 1 cup berries and place on top of second layer.
For final layer, mix remaining 4 ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour onto third layer.
Place in refrigerator and let set.

title: coffee bread
directions: Roll up.
Turn into ring and place on Reynold's Wrap.
Slice every inch or so through first layer of dough.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate two hours before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator about 1 week.

title: easter baba
directions: Scald milk; slowly add 3/4 cup flour to hot milk and beat thoroughly; cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup milk and 1 tablespoon sugar; add to cooled mixture and beat well.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Add salt to eggs and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar and continue to beat.
Add flavorings and remaining flour.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Add butter; continue kneading for 10 minutes, or until dough leaves the fingers.
Add almonds, fruit peels, or both, if desired.
Mix well.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Punch down and divide into 2 parts.
Place in greased pans, or into fluted tube pan (10-inch).
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 325°
for 40 minutes.
Decorate with white lucre.
Sprinkle with colored sugar or baker's confetti.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion with seasoning mix.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cheese and sour cream and layer over meat mixture.
Add the crescent rolls over the cheese mixture.
Spread dough out flat.
Mix Parmesan cheese and margarine.
Spoon over dough.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes. Let cool completely before topping.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken.
Salt to taste.
When done, drain and save broth.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and put aside.
Chop onion and bell pepper and saute in oleo.
Cut cheese into small cubes.
Cook vermicelli in broth, drain and add cheese while hot.

title: 3 day coconut sour cream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions; cool.
Split layers to make 4 layers.
While cake is baking, combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Blend well.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup of sugar/sour cream/coconut mixture.
With remaining sugar mixture, frost layers.
To reserved 1 cup of mixture, add 8 ounces Cool Whip. Then frost top and sides with this.
Refrigerate in airtight container.
Keep for 3 days in refrigerator before serving.

title: bill's lasagna
directions: Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spray with Pam.
Put a thin layer of sauce in bottom of dish.
Place 3 lasagna noodles in dish (to cover bottom).
Top with more sauce.
Place 24 pepperoni slices on noodles.
Do this by making 4 rows of 6 pepperoni slices, going across the noodles.
Sprinkle approximately 6 ounces of cheese over dish.
Repeat steps for 4 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into 12 slices.

title: mom's spice cake
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar and shortening.
Save 1 heaping cup for topping.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: bill's clam chowder
directions: Boil vegetables in water about 1/2 hour or until soft.
Add clams and juice.
Cook fresh clams 8 to 10 minutes.
Add milk, butter and spices to taste.

title: porky pine meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form medium-size balls. Brown balls in deep fat.
Place in baking dish.

title: "amazin raisin cake"
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round baking pans.
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed beat the first 10 ingredients 2 minutes. Stir in apples, raisins, and nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes in pans and remove.
Frost with sour cream frosting when cool.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Cook vegetables in water until tender, about 20 minutes. Brown beef.
Add beef to vegetables, juices and spices.
Cook about 40 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix
together first four ingredients and cook in double boiler.
Cook 1 minute.
Add vanilla.

title: bill's turkey dressing
directions: Brown hamburger and pork sausage; set aside.
Chop celery, green pepper, onion and parsley; saute in butter until tender. Heat chicken broth; pour over bread cubes.
Add rest of ingredients and then add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Taste and add any seasonings you think it needs.

title: cheezy vegetable soup(lighter eating - 1 point)
directions: Put all veggies, tomatoes, and broth in pot and bring to a boil. Then add your cheese, melt thoroughly. Once melted it is ready to eat.

title: off-the-bone chicken wings
directions: Wash and dry chicken wings.
Place chicken into a container or Ziploc bag and add 2 tablespoons of sauce, 1 tablespoon of oil and pepper to taste.
Marinate overnight or no less than 1 hour (cook's choice).

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Bring eggs, margarine or butter and buttermilk to room temperature.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In small mixing bowl, stir together flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat margarine or butter with electric mixer on medium speed until softened.
Gradually add sugar, beating until well combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each and scraping bowl frequently.
Add lemon peel, juice and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to beaten mixture, beating after each addition just until combined.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.
Drizzle with Lemon Icing.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: You also need a 4-quart freezer. For 6-quart, increase by 1/2.

title: sourdough drop biscuits
directions: Mix starter and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with starter.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in saucepan until done.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fettuccine primavera
directions: Saute chicken and onions in olive oil until white.
Add veggies and saute 2 more minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce and shrimp. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until shrimp is cooked and chicken is cooked through.
Stir in spinach; cook to 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles, topped with cheese.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill well.

title: sombrero pie
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except pastry.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare pastry.
Pour meat mixture into ungreased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches. Cover with pastry; seal to edges of baking dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and beans until well blended. Spread mixture on a plate or round pizza pan. Cover with salsa, and top with shredded cheese.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Peel carrots and shred them.
Mix the shredded carrots with the raisins and mayonnaise.
Serve and eat.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: wild onions
directions: Onions should be picked when they are young and tender. Most people don't
know	what wild onions are.
This is a real Indian food for Cherokee.

title: hominy spoon bread
directions: *A dedicated Rebel would use buttermilk with 2 pinches of soda!

title: tangy beef dip
directions: Soak dried onion flakes in white or red wine.
Blend by hand all ingredients.
Chill and serve with wheat crackers.

title: golden lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
In a skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Add soup mix blended with water.
Place lemon on chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over rice.

title: round mounds
directions: Mix and set aside in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Make small balls and dip in following chocolate coating:

title: bran pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, combine yeast and warm water; stir until dissolved.
Add bran; let stand 5 minutes to soften.
In medium bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar and salt.
Using wooden spoon, stir into bran mixture until well combined.
Gradually add remaining flour if dough is too sticky to handle.
Place on floured board; knead until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Cover with towel.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Divide dough into 12 pieces; roll each into 13-inch rope.
Form into pretzel shape.
Place on prepared cookie sheet.
Brush lightly with egg.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 pretzels.

title: oven french toast
directions: Set oven at 300°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet with sides with butter.
Mix eggs, milk and vanilla flavoring together with a fork.
Using a fork, dip both sides of the bread into the mixture and place on the cookie sheet.
Pour any remaining mixture over the bread.
Bake in the oven 10 minutes.
Remove from the oven.
Turn each piece over with a spatula.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Serve with maple syrup, cinnamon, jam or brown sugar.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add next 6 items.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Combine meat mixture and remaining ingredients in large bowl or platter; toss.
Serves 4 people.

title: dog food on toast
directions: Scramble the hamburger and sausage.
Drain all of the fat. Add the cheese, which has been cut into small chunks.
Keep the heat on until all of the cheese has melted.
Place the meat mixture on top of the bread and place under the broiler for a few minutes.

title: angel hair pasta with chicken
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil and add chicken; cook about 5 minutes and drain on paper towel. Add the other tablespoon of oil and add carrots (optional) and cook 2 minutes. Cook pasta; while this cooks, add chicken broth, basil and Parmesan to skillet and stir well. Return chicken to skillet and reduce heat. Simmer about 4 minutes. Drain pasta and place in bowl or platter; top with chicken in skillet and serve.

title: "sarah's organic tomato sauce"
directions: Cook onion in saucepan with olive oil until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, basil, sea salt, pepper and water.
Mix well and simmer sauce for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: caramel korn
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 7 minutes.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: wild rice harvest casserole
directions: Brown chicken and celery in butter.
In a large bowl combine soup and broth until smooth.
Add mushrooms, onion, rice, poultry seasonings and chicken mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir and sprinkle with cashews.
Return to oven for 15 minutes or until rice is tender. Serves 8.

title: spinach pinwheels
directions: Cook, drain and cool spinach.
Mix together all ingredients, except tortillas.
Spread on flour tortillas a thin layer of mixture.
Roll up.
Put on cookie sheet and cover well.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices with sharp serrated knife.
Arrange on plate.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put all ingredients together and put in microwave safe bowl. Microwave until melted.
Stir often.
Dip with nachos.

title: vegetable cheese burrito
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well and set aside.
Place tortillas on a baking sheet coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Top each tortilla evenly with 1/4 cup cheese. Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 minutes or just until cheese melts.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour, salt, pepper and mustard. Cook, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Add milk gradually. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Stir small amount of milk mixture into egg yolk; stir egg mixture into milk mixture in saucepan.
Cook for 1 minute longer.
Layer half the cabbage, onion, cheese and cream sauce in baking dish; repeat layer.
Top with crumbs.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove cover; bake for 5 minutes longer.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg and ketchup in a large bowl.
Add meat, crumbs, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper; mix well. Shape into loaf; place in baking dish.

title: dietetic apple cake
directions: Combine raisins, water and 1 packet sweetener in small saucepan.
Simmer over medium heat until all water is absorbed.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in slightly salted water (8 minutes).
Drain; add soup, pimentos and chestnuts.
Mix oleo, bread crumbs and almonds. Sprinkle on casserole.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, until bubbly at 350°.

title: quickie beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into strips; brown in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add onion and garlic; cook 5 minutes.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, ketchup and Worcestershire.
Add to meat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: beefy bunwiches
directions: Scald milk; stir in salt and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir milk mixture into yeast.
Add flour and mix well.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: chicken tetrazzini(serves a lot)
directions: Mix together and sprinkle on the chicken breasts the 2 tablespoons salt, onion salt and celery salt.
Cover chicken with water and simmer 1 hour.
Save broth.
Remove skin and bones and chop into chunks.
Place in large bowl.

title: pineapple-orange sherbet
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
If blender stalls, you may need to stir ingredients and/or add a little more juice before continuing blending.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: In a soup pot, combine corned beef, bay leaf, peppercorn, onion, sliced carrot and celery, parsley and cider.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Skim off any surface scum. Lower heat and cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove corned beef to a platter.
Keep warm.
Add halved carrots and potatoes to pot.
Cook 15 minutes.
Surround corned beef with vegetables.
Serve mustard and horseradish.

title: apple pie(norway)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix apples, lemon juice, vanilla, chopped nuts and eggs together, then add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Place sliced, peeled apples in 9-inch baking dish. Mix dry ingredients and break the egg over them.
Mix like dough until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Melt butter and pour over all. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream or custard.

title: quick and easy refrigerator rolls(no cholesterol)
directions: Stir ingredients together in order given.
Refrigerate dough at least 12 hours.
(Dough may be kept in refrigerator for several days.)
Roll dough into your favorite shape on a lightly floured board; let rise 2 hours before baking.
I make plain dinner rolls, pecan rolls and cinnamon rolls with this recipe.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Number of servings: 3 dozen.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into two balls or logs. Sprinkle with paprika and roll in pecans.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Can be frozen.

title: stuffed tortilla rolls(serves 12)
directions: Mix cream cheese, chillies, olives, green onions, cumin and garlic powder in food processor or mixer. Spread on tortillas. Roll them up and individually wrap in foil. Chill them overnight. Makes 6 to 8 tortillas. Unwrap and slice. Serve with picante sauce.

title: saucy pineapple cake
directions: In saucepan, combine undrained pineapple, pudding mix and 1/3 cup water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.

Prepare cake mix according to package directions; pour batter over pineapple mixture in pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 10 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
Makes 9 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well the diced, raw apples and sugar.
Add cooking oil, beaten eggs, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Bake for 1 hour in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350°.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting when cooled.

title: rice and meat balls
directions: Mix all together and make into balls.
Roll in rice.
Place in large casserole dish.

title: quick chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cook about 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken fried round steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Pound steak thoroughly or ask meat man to do it.
Mix eggs and milk.
Dip meat into egg mixture, then into cracker crumbs.
Brown slowly on both sides in hot oil. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly.
Cook over very low heat for 45 to 60 minutes, or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Fry cabbage and onion until tender.
Brown hamburger.
Add hamburger or tomato paste to cabbage and onion mixture.
Simmer about 5 minutes.

title: chicken and asparagus
directions: Sprinkle pepper on chicken. Saute chicken in oil slowly for 6 minutes over medium heat. Remove and drain on paper.
Cook asparagus for 4 to 5 minutes. Drain and place in a 9 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Next, place chicken over asparagus.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Cream butter, add syrup, vanilla and salt.
Beat well and add cocoa.
Gradually add sugar and milk alternately.
Beat until smooth.
Yields enough for a 2 layer cake.

title: chicken orzo salad
directions: Cook and drain orzo according to directions.
Cook and cube chicken.
Cut grapes in half.
Mix all (orzo, chicken, grapes, almonds, pineapple and Marzetti) together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
(Must do this overnight or at least 10 hours!)

title: green beans vinaigrette
directions: Add the pimiento, parsley, chives or green onion and cucumber pickle to the French dressing.
Serve over cold cooked green beans.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix white sugar with cinnamon. Melt butter. Roll biscuits individually in butter, then cinnamon & sugar and place in baking pan (a metal gelatin ring mold works very well).
Bake around 20 minutes at 350 degrees and check. You may want to turn out onto another baking sheet so that it finishes baking evenly.

Add powdered sugar gradually to any left over melted butter (melt more if needed). Add milk and vanilla as desired to make frosting. Apply thick frosting to hot biscuits; it will thin some as it melts.
Garnish with maraschino cherries if you want!

title: baked stew
directions: Put steak in bottom of flat Pyrex.
Add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over all a small can of tomato juice.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour with dish covered tightly with foil.
Cook potatoes separately.
Serves 6.

title: fried cheese cubes
directions: Cut cheese into 3-inch cubes and dip in egg; coat with combined crumbs and sesame seed.
Repeat.
Fry in deep hot oil at 350° for 1 or 2 minutes or until browned.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef in thin strips.
Season with salt and pepper and dredge lightly with flour.
Cook beef, onion and garlic in oil until lightly browned.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add sour cream but do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Blend or puree together all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Add salt and Parmesan cheese to taste.
(You may freeze pesto for later use.)
To make a creamy pesto, mix with yogurt before serving.

title: the ninety calorie banana split
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in medium bowl. Stir in cold water.
Pour mixture slowly into an 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Cut gelatin into 1/2-inch cubes.
Divide gelatin cubes into 4 dessert dishes. Halve and split bananas.
Just before serving, place 2 pieces in each dish.
Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with walnuts.

title: devilish crab eggs
directions: Peel the hard-cooked eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
Put in bowl and mash well.
Add celery, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add the crab meat and mix well.
Stuff the egg whites with the yolk mixture.
Chill before serving.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken breasts, celery, salt, onion, Hellmann's mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
When it comes out of oven, pour icing mixture on it.
Sprinkle generously with nuts.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and set aside to cool.
Place cake mix in bowl.
Add cooled Jell-O, eggs, oil and flavoring.
Beat until well mixed.
Line tube pan with wax paper, bottom only. Grease and dust with flour.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°. Remove from pan at once.
Glaze while hot.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add fruits with juices.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Pour into 2-quart dish and put into refrigerator, stirring occasionally, until begins to congeal.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Add milk and dry ingredients alternately. Beat until batter is smooth. Add vanilla. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sunny salad
directions: Mix dressing and ginger until well blended. Refrigerate. Arrange fruit and cheese over mixed greens on salad plates. Serve with dressing mixture. Variation: Substitute 1/4 tsp. cinnamon for ginger.

title: crab soup
directions: Combine crab meat, soup and half and half cream in saucepan. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Do not let bottom burn.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add a little lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Serve with a thin slice of lemon floating on top and a little fresh parsley.
Serves 4 to 5.
(I have doubled and re-doubled this recipe to serve a crowd with great results.)

title: carrot pecan cake
directions: Mix as usual for cakes.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool upright in pan.

title: cheese stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
After standing time, halve potatoes lengthwise and carefully scoop out inside.
Set shells aside.
Combine potatoes, butter, milk, salt and pepper in medium mixing bowl. Mash until fluffy.

title: easy cake mix cookies
directions: Add eggs, butter and water to any cake mix.
For really soft cookies, use 1/4 cup water.
Form dough into a roll.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice or drop from a spoon for drop cookies.
Roll into balls and flatten if you want to decorate cookies.
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 8 minutes.

title: kielbasa appetizer
directions: Simmer onion in margarine until softened.
Add apple juice, sugar and ketchup to onion.
Slice and quarter 1/4-inch slices of Kielbasa; add to sauce and simmer for 1 hour.
Keep warm while serving with toothpicks.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix Crisco with these ingredients until flour crumbs.
Pour in buttermilk.
Bake at 425° until brown on top and bottom.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green
beans
until
dry.	Add soup and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour in casserole dish and top with remaining onions. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Will serve 8.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: In bowl, beat eggs; add next 7 ingredients and mix well.
Work in beef with your hands.
Stir in cheese and cover any cheese that shows.
Put in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix lightly.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 sandwiches.

title: artichoke relish
directions: Wash and grind artichokes.
Cover with 3/4 cup salt.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Grind onions and peppers.
Bring vinegar to a boil and add mustard seed and celery seed.
Boil 15 minutes.
Mix sugar, flour, turmeric, dry mustard, cinnamon and black pepper. Add a little water to make a paste.
Add enough hot vinegar to dissolve.
Add gradually to hot vinegar.
Boil 15 minutes. Squeeze salt from artichokes.
Combine artichokes, onions and bell peppers to vinegar mix.
Bring to a boil.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 17 to 18 pints.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat into strips.
In skillet brown meat in oil.
Remove meat from skillet; add gravy and water bringing to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients except noodles.
Return meat to skillet.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
When done, serve over hot noodles.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Remove casings from sausage.
Cook sausage, ground beef, onion, celery and garlic in a large skillet until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir to crumble meat.
Drain well. Stir in tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Dip eggplant slices in eggs; coat with cracker crumbs. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy skillet.
Arrange a single layer of eggplant slices in skillet and brown on both sides.
Drain eggplant on paper towels; set aside.
Repeat with remaining eggplant.
Layer half eggplant in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon half of sauce mixture over eggplant slices; repeat layers.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts in 4 cups of water and salt. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove meat from bone and set aside.
Reserve 2 cups of broth.
Combine next 4 ingredients and salt and pepper; cook in reserved broth, stirring constantly (cook on medium heat until it comes to boil).
Dissolve cornstarch in warm water.
Pour into vegetables.
Add chicken. Pour into double crust pie shell.
Perforate the top crust.
Cook 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: chicken paella
directions: Cook chicken strips until no longer pink.
Remove from pan. Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add broth, uncooked rice, oregano, paprika, salt, pepper and saffron.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer covered 15 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, several peppers and frozen peas to skillet.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes more until rice is tender.
Stir in cooked chicken.
Cook and stir 1 minute or more until heated through.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, green pepper, rice, salt, pepper, onion, parsley, egg and milk in bowl; mix well.
Shape into approximately 18 meat balls and place in kettle.
Add can of whole tomatoes and water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue tom's wonderful weak fish
directions: Assemble in foil packet.
Grill 10 minutes on barbecue or assemble in baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: lori's lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; stir water in gradually. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Slowly stir half the hot mixture into 3 egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Pour this mixture back into remaining hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute longer. Remove from heat; continue stirring until smooth.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour into already baked pie shell and chill.
Cover with whipped cream and enjoy.

title: oatmeal-bran muffins
directions: Pour water over bran and set aside.
Mix oil, applesauce, sugar, eggs and buttermilk in medium sized mixing bowl.
In large bowl, mix flour, salt, soda and oats.
Add to flour mixture both other mixtures and stir until combined.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Batter may be refrigerated up to 6 weeks.

title: savory pork roast
directions: Rub pork roast with cut sides of garlic.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle on pork.
Place pork, fat side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer.
Roast, uncovered, at 325° until meat thermometer registers 170°, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Garnish with frosted grapes, if desired.
(Dip grapes in water, then roll in sugar.)

title: sara's cinnamon buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
In a large bowl put 3 cups flour; stir in milk, sugar, Crisco, baking powder, salt and egg.
Mix until smooth.
Add yeast mixture and enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead for 5 minutes until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise in a warm place, about 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Divide dough in 3 parts.
Place 1/3 dough on floured board and roll into an oblong shape, approximately 1/2 inch thick.

title: shrimp with garlic
directions: Rinse shrimp. Pat dry. Set aside. In your vessel, heat the oil and butter over moderate heat. (This can be prepared on a grill or in oven.) When hot (not smoking), add the garlic, thyme, crushed peppers, Worcestershire sauce and shrimp. Toss to coat with oil and butter and cook, stirring occasionally, just until the shrimp are pink (4 to 5 minutes). With a slotted spoon, remove the shrimp to a warm platter. Sprinkle lightly with the salt and with the parsley. I serve this dish as a low country dinner with newspaper covering the table and with finger bowls and extra napkins for each guest.

title: cafe vienna mix
directions: Place sugar in a small bowl and sprinkle with almond and vanilla extracts.
With a fork, stir and blend until no trace of extract moisture remains.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Sift to blend thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 1/2 cups mix.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and add 7-Up.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch pan to chill.
Mix together pineapple (reserve juice), marshmallows and bananas.
Add to jello mixture and return to refrigerator until firm.
Stir together pineapple juice, egg, flour and sugar.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter.
Cool and spread over top of jello.
Before serving, spread with whipped topping.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: Let milk sour for a couple of minutes.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs; add mashed bananas.
To this mixture, add milk, flour, soda and salt.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake in well-greased bread pan. (I also flour my bread pan.)
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and keep in refrigerator.

title: ozark mountain potatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Add potatoes and onions to the bacon grease and fry until lightly browned.
Salt and pepper then add the bacon.
Add just enough water to barely cover and simmer slowly about 15 minutes until the water cooks away.
When water is gone, turn potatoes and finish browning and crisping.

title: brownies
directions: Place one stick margarine in pan.
Add Wesson oil.
Add cocoa and water.
Place this in pot and bring to a boil.
Then pour mixture over flour, sugar and buttermilk.
Stir mix.
Then add baking soda, vanilla and eggs; mix well again.
Then pour into greased and floured pan, 17 x 11 x 3/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: southwest appetizer cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add taco seasoning and ranch dressing. Add all other ingredients. Simmer for several hours.
Can use a crockpot.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Mix 3 or 4 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water for a nice cup of hot tea.

title: lemon meringue pies
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cold water together.
Add this to the boiling water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add to the egg yolks, lemon juice and butter or oleo.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Cool.
Put in baked pie shells.

title: crab spread
directions: In 1/2-inch deep dish, spread 1/4-inch layer of cream cheese. Top with crab meat and top with layer of seafood sauce.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.
(Great.)

title: fat free and sugar free harvest bread
directions: Grease eight no. 2 cans.
Fill about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before taking out of can.
Slice and spread with cream cheese and orange marmalade.

title: taco tartlets
directions: To Make Meat Shells:
Combine ground beef, taco seasoning mix and ice water; mix well.
Press meat mixture into bottom and up sides of mini muffin pans; set aside.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise and dressing with beater.
Add to the mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix all contents together and put into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: raspberry cheese pie
directions: Crust:
Blend pecans, brown sugar, cinnamon and cloves in processor.
Transfer to bowl.
Mix in the melted butter, press in the bottom of spring-form pan (9-inch).
Press up sides, chill 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake the crust until golden brown, about 20 minutes, cool completely on rack.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Shred the chicken breasts.
Mix all together chicken breasts, cream of mushroom soup, peas, mushrooms, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and croutons.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Put into casserole dish.
Drain green beans. Mix green beans, mushroom soup, onion and cheese.
Pour on top of hamburger.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until brown.

title: shortbread christmas cookies
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar and flour.
Chill.
Cut out.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all together at one time.
Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 300° to 350° for about an hour.

title: energy crunch cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan butter, sugar, milk and salt; stirring bring to boil.
Boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix. Pour into 13 x 9-inch buttered pan. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and boiling water.
Cook to lukewarm. Mix cold water and yeast.
Add to first mixture.
Beat in eggs; add flour and salt.
Place dough in bowl, cover and place in refrigerator.
Make out rolls as you need them 2 to 2 1/2 hours before baking at 375° to 400° until done.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple, mix instant pudding with pineapple; add marshmallows, Cool Whip, cottage cheese and nuts.
Mix well.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and garlic until yellow.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
With 2 knives, cut up and blend ingredients.
Simmer sauce, uncovered, about 20 minutes until slightly thick.

title: silver spoon wings
directions: Combine sugar, water, soy sauce, pineapple juice, oil, ginger and garlic powder.
Stir
until sugar dissolves.
Pour over chicken
and refrigerate 1 or 2 days. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot punch
directions: Heat to boiling point and serve.
Sprinkle a little brown sugar on top.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, sugar and brown sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs. Gradually beat flour mixture.
Add morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls to ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 9 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand for 2 minutes and remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble and place in bottom of pie shell.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Arrange over bacon. Place half of ham and 2 slices cheese over onions.
Repeat layers of ham and cheese.
Beat eggs and mustard together.
Add to warm cream and beat again.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: southwestern success
directions: Prepare rice according to directions on package.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice and cheese.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add cooked rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: wassail
directions: Simmer together and serve hot.

title: chocolate mousse with kahlua
directions: Melt chocolate bits in Kahlua in top of double boiler.
In blender, mix orange juice, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Add melted chocolate mixture and heavy cream and blend again.
Pour into serving dishes and refrigerate from 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with a dab of whipped cream or Cool Whip and sprinkle chocolate shavings on top.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Add soda to dates.
Add water and let cool.
Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs and the date mixture.
Add flour, cocoa, salt, vanilla and 1/2 package chocolate chips.
Pour this batter in a cake pan and sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 package of chocolate chips over the top.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lemon chiffon dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers sugar and oleo together for the crust. Press into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Dissolve jello, cool, mix cream cheese and sugar and vanilla, slowly add cool whip. Pour over crust.

title: chili relleno dish
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer cheese and chilies and repeat. Mix flour, milk and eggs and pour over chilies. Bake at 425° covered for 30 minutes. Uncover and pour 1 cup salsa over chilies and bake 20 minutes more.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain in very thin strips.
In skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook 1/2 the beef and onion until meat is no longer pink.
Set aside.
Repeat with remaining margarine, beef and onion.
Return meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa powder.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside. In a large bowl, blend sugars with an electric mixer at medium speed.
Add butter and beat to form a grainy paste.
Scrape sides of bowl, then add eggs and mint extract.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add the flour mixture and chocolate chips; blend at low speed just until combined.

title: ohio lasagna
directions: Brown chicken.
Add onion, mushrooms, tomato sauce and paste. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Prepare noodles separately using a tablespoon of oil in water to prevent sticking.
Drain and spread each noodle.
Ready to layer.
Alternate layer sauce, noodles and cheeses in 13 x 9 1/4-inch casserole.
Repeat.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine
sugar,
margarine, syrup and vanilla in saucepan; bring
to
a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add baking
soda.
Pour over popcorn in a large roasting pan; stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes. Remove from oven; cool and serve.

title: garden soup
directions: In large heavy nonstick kettle or Dutch oven, cook onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and 5 cups water.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender; drain.
Beat egg in milk, Pam a square dish.
Layer macaroni and cheese, repeat, then pour milk and egg mixture over macaroni and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: caramel brownies(yummy!)
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk.
Mix chocolate mix, evaporated milk, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Spread 1/2 of the batter in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle a 6 ounce package of chocolate chips over hot batter. Drizzle melted caramels over the chocolate chips.
Crumble or drop the remaining batter in small pieces over the melted caramels. Bake 16 minutes longer at 350° (no longer).

title: chocolate cake(25 to 30 minutes)
directions: Sift flour; measure, resift with sugar and salt.
Put oleo, shortening and cocoa in a saucepan; bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk, vanilla and cinnamon. Mix well.
Pour in a well-greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(If you use a 9 x 13-inch pan cooking time will vary.)
Frost cake hot from the oven.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well and let set out of refrigerator all day, 8 to 12 hours, until very bubbly.
Feed 2 or 3 times before making bread to avoid depleting your Starter.
Take out one cup to make bread and return the rest to the refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk together.
Add Cool Whip before pudding mixture is set.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish layer as follows:

title: swiss chicken
directions: Cook the chicken breasts, debone and dice.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Mix the soup and broth.
Pour over the chicken. Cover with the cheese slices.
Sprinkle with the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or toast.

title: dill cheese bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water in bowl and set aside.
Heat cottage cheese.
Do not boil.
Add cottage cheese to yeast and water.
Now add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place on floured board.
Knead and shape into loaf.
Snip top.
Grease top.
Let rise in pan until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 or 35 minutes.
Excellent toasted.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Heat oil and stir in the crackers. Add the rest of the ingredients and stir well.

title: meat-filled tacos
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until done.
Drain off fat.
Stir in taco seasoning mix and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, arrange taco shells on a baking sheet lined with paper towels.
Warm in a 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stuff each taco shell with meat, tomatoes, cheese, lettuce and top with taco sauce.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Slice a pound cake and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle orange juice over pound cake.
Add a thick layer of fresh fruit; can be mixed or fruit of choice.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk; when thick, add part of container of Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture over fresh fruit.
Spread rest of Cool Whip over the top.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: shrimp or crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Needs to set several hours (refrigerated).

title: hot crab dip
directions: In large bowl, blend cream cheese, sour cream, salad dressing, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and garlic.
Add milk to make mixture creamy.
(Additional milk, if needed.)
Stir in 2 tablespoons cheese, fold in crab meat, pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° approximately 30 minutes or until bubbles show and top is light brown.
Garnish.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and sugar; press into 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: cranberry wassail
directions: Tie nutmeg, cinnamon and allspice in a cheesecloth bag.
Take with tea bags and brew 3/4 hour in the 2 1/2 cups water.
Add sugar, cranberry juice, 1 1/2 cups water, orange juice and lemon juice.
Serve piping hot.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: foil dessert
directions: Slice donut in half lengthwise.
Place one slice of pineapple in between donut halves.
Place marshmallows in donut "hole". Wrap in aluminum foil.
Place in coals for about 5 to 10 minutes until warm and marshmallows are melted.

title: sweet potato with apples
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; cool slightly and peel off skins. Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Layer potatoes in greased oblong (10 x 6) dish, then apples over top.
Pour orange juice over all.
Mix brown sugar, ginger and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples. Dot with butter or oleo.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix apples and sugar set aside.
Grease and flour an oblong cake pan.
Add margarine and eggs to apple mixture.
Mix in flour, baking powder, nutmeg, soda, and cinnamon. Pour into a pan (larger size the better).
Sprinkle top with a little table sugar and bake for 45 minutes, watching for it to turn dark golden brown.

title: easy ground meat casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion until done; drain.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Combine all ingredients; pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple to make 1 cup juice.
Put in saucepan and bring to boil.
Add pineapple; remove from heat.
Mix Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water and 1 1/2 cups of cold water.
Mix pineapple in Jell-O, then add marshmallows.
Chill until almost firm, then add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: deluxe broccoli casserole
directions: Blend first three ingredients together; stir in cheese and broccoli.
Pour into buttered, 2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings. You can make 1/2 receipt.

title: mock watermelon rind pickles
directions: Large overgrown cucumbers that are beginning to turn yellow are ideal for these pickles.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cut shortening into flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Stir well.
Put mixture on floured surface.
Knead a little and roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Great to make ahead; will keep 3 or 4 days in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° approximately 10 minutes.

title: end-of-the-month casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Combine with cabbage, carrots, rice, soup, water, pepper and cumin in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, for an hour.
Or cover dish with plastic wrap and cook on High (100%) power in microwave oven for 15 to 20 minutes, stopping twice to stir.
The casserole is done when cabbage and carrots are tender.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: marcia's tex-mex layered dip
directions: On bottom of 2-quart glass casserole dish (not too deep), spread browned hamburger and refried beans.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning and layer on top of hamburger/beans.
Next, layer picante sauce.
Continue layering remaining ingredients, ending with Cheddar cheese.
Cover and chill.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: bar-b-que chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Fry until lightly browned.
Place in roaster or baking dish and bake at 350°F for 1 1/2 hrs.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour on chicken and bake for 1 1/2 hrs. longer.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Beat cake mixes, eggs and oil (batter will be very stiff). Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased baking sheets and flatten slightly. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until a slight indentation remains when lightly touched. Cool.

title: holiday cheese nut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into 2 balls.
Roll in reserved chopped nuts.
Garnish with cherries and fresh parsley. Chill before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients in order. Roll in balls. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: steamed vegetables with cheddar cheese sauce
directions: Saute vegetables until tender.
Pour on serving plate.
Top with soup.
Serve over cooked rice or as vegetable dish.

title: paella
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Combine all the ingredients.
Pour mixture into a baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake about 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: anymeal skillet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in cubes; cover.
Cook in oil until potatoes are half done.
Add onions and wieners.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: hot mexican dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Add corn, barbecue sauce and Cheez Whiz.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add chili powder. Put some Fritos on top.
Heat in 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo.
Boil 1 minute. Add salt, vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well. Drop on cookie sheet or foil.
Let stand until cool.

title: quick apple bread pudding
directions: In a deep dish or pan of any size you choose, put a layer of slices of bread until bottom is covered.
Next, combine apples, sugar, beaten egg, nutmeg, cinnamon and milk.
Spread apple mixture over slices of bread.
Alternate a layer of bread, then a layer of apples until pan is full.

title: beef oriental
directions: Heat oil and add beef and cook quickly until browned.
Combine soy sauce, water and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Pour over beef. Bring to a boil and add sliced onions and pepper.
Cook on high for 4 minutes.
To thicken, add 1 tablespoon of cornstarch, blended with 2 tablespoons of cold water.
Add to mixture and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Good over rice!

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir sausage and onion in 3-quart saucepan until sausage is light brown.
Drain fat off.
Stir in tomatoes, garbanzo beans, broth, water, zucchini and basil.
(Break up tomatoes with fork before adding to soup.)
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until zucchini is tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve and let each person add Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and spices; add pumpkin.
Beat egg yolks; add milk and pour into pumpkin mixture.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and margarine; mix well.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Pour into baked shell.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as instructed on box.
Cool it.
Chop green onions and whole pepper.
Drain marinated artichoke hearts and save liquid.
Slice artichoke hearts in halves.
Mix all ingredients.
To the liquid of the artichokes, add mayonnaise and curry powder; toss with other ingredients and serve cold.

title: chicken dressing and giblet gravy(50 years or older)
directions: Bring broth to boil.
Break eggs into broth, stirring until done.
Place both breads in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour broth over bread mixture.
Toss lightly until crumbs are damp, not soggy.

title: baked or stuffed tomatoes
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet with onion and celery and cook over low heat until onions are clear.
Add tomatoes and bring to a boil, about 2 minutes.
Add bread crumbs (saving some for top) and stir well.
Add parsley and meat, if desired.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole and dot with butter and slices of bacon.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until the top is brown.
Serves 4.
May be used with fresh tomatoes as well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese and pineapple until smooth.
Add 1 cup pecans and remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Shape into one or 2 balls. Roll in remaining pecans.
Chill.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Add all ingredients and beat until batter is liquid.
Pour into buttered spring form pan, then place in water in broiler pan. Bake at 350 for 65 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave cake for another 30 minutes with the door shut and then 30 minutes with the door open.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: elizabeth's cole slaw
directions: Combine
mayonnaise,
sugar, salt, pepper, celery seed, vinegar and oil; then pour over shredded cabbage.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots until tender; drain.
Cook celery and onions in 1 quart water with bouillon cubes added.
Combine vegetables, soup and Velveeta.
Heat thoroughly.
Microwave or steam broccoli 5 minutes.
Add as last ingredient before serving.

title: rhubarb and strawberry jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar together.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello. Mix together and put in glasses and cover.
Must be kept in refrigerator.

title: souper burgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion in shortening.
Stir to separate meat.
Add next 4 ingredients and cook 5 minutes, stirring now and then.
Serve on buns.
Garnish with onion and tomato slices.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: chicken pie
directions: Toss melted margarine with stuffing.
Cover top with crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Combine both until flour is all moistened.
This will keep in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: easy drop rolls
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Add all other ingredients and stir. Dough will be soft and sticky.
Place in an airtight container and store in refrigerator several hours before using.
(Dough will keep a week.)

title: charlotte's brownie trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix to make cake brownies (better if you use the one that has walnuts in the mix with it).
Bake in 13x9x2 pan. Cool.
Crumble in small pieces.

Prepare pudding mix per directions on box but omit chilling. (Sugar free is good, too.) Place 1/2 of crumbled brownie mix in three quarter trifle bowl. Top with half of the pudding mix, half of the crushed candy pieces, and half of the cool whip.
Repeat layers.
Garnish with chocolate curls, cover with saran wrap, and chill for at least eight hours before serving.

title: brown sugar gelatin salad
directions: Combine gelatin and cold water.
When dissolved good add the next four ingredients.
Combine all and add remaining ingredients. Can be put in a serving dish or a square baking dish.

title: canned salmon
directions: Fill 4 pint jars with 1 inch chunks of salmon only to the neck of jar.
Put lids on.
Use 1 quart water in pressure cooker with rack plus 1 tablespoon of vinegar to keep jars from becoming cloudy.
Pressure at 10 pounds for 90 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes, then tighten caps.

title: mix cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350°.

title: doughnut muffins
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients.
Add egg and beat well.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add alternately with milk to egg mixture.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove at once and roll in melted butter, then in brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Makes 12 medium sized muffins or 18 small ones.

title: amber's banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, add vanilla pudding and skim milk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Add as many cookies and bananas as desired.
You may add a sprinkle of cinnamon or pineapple, if desired.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moist.
Do not beat! Stir in vanilla, pineapple,
nuts and bananas.
Spoon into well-greased cake pans.
Best done as layer cake but you can substitute a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Melt butter; saut onion and celery about 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and seasoning.
Add diced potatoes and cover with water; cook uncovered over medium heat about 15 minutes until potatoes are soft.
When most of water is evaporated, add parsley, milk and evaporated milk.
Add clams and juice and cook over low heat about 10 to 15 minutes (do not overcook).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients until creamy.
Add dry ingredients. Blend well.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
May also add raisins, nuts or chocolate chips.

title: south dakota meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first eight ingredients. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Press into an ungreased 8 x 4 x 2 in. loaf pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 1 1/4 hours; drain.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: picalilli
directions: Remove seeds from peppers. Chop vegetables very fine. Arrange vegetables in layers, sprinkling each layer with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 12 pints.

title: caponata
directions: Cut off stems and take out seeds of hot cherry peppers.
Mix 2 parts water to one part vinegar.
Soak pepper shells in brine for 12 hours.
Drain well.
Stuff with 1 to 2 anchovies, depending on size of pepper.
Ready to eat or put in jar and cover with oil to seal.
Amounts depend on quantity desired.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter for 2 minutes.
In large pan, bring broth and chicken cubes to a boil; add onion mixture and noodles. Boil for 12 minutes; add cooked broccoli, milk and pepper.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Cook at low temperature until noodles are done.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cheese together.
Add lemon juice.
Chop cucumber very fine and add to cheese mixture.
Add remaining ingredients plus a dash of Tabasco, garlic salt and seasoned pepper.
Chill and serve on bread.

title: spaghetti cabonari
directions: Cook spaghetti. In large skillet, cook bacon.
Pour off fat. Remove bacon.
Saute onions and pepper in butter.
Stir in cooked spaghetti.
Add crumbled bacon. Add eggs and stir until eggs are done.
Mix well. Put on plates and add Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.
Serves 4 hungry people.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix in the order given.
Shape dough into balls and place on baking sheet.
Dip a fork or glass bottom in granulated sugar, then use to flatten cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. This is a large recipe which will make about 100 cookies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook potatoes and mash.
Combine all ingredients except the marshmallows.
Spoon mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with marshmallows and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until the marshmallows are golden brown.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix all together; add enough salmon liquid to hold together. Mold into soft ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: susan's wacky cake
directions: In the sifter, combine the flour, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Sift into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Make 3 holes in this dry mixture.
Into one hole, pour the oil; into the next, the vinegar; into the next, the vanilla.
Pour the cold water over it. Beat with a spoon until it's nearly smooth and you can't see any more flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bayou broccoli(microwave)
directions: Heat butter in 3-quart casserole 1
to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in onion and celery.
Heat 4 to 6 minutes until tender.
Combine cheese, soup and water in small bowl.
Blend well.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes until cheese melts.
Stir into onion mixture.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Blend well.
Heat 6 to 9 minutes.
Stir once. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and let stand 2 minutes.

title: cornbread mix
directions: Combine and mix well.
Store in airtight container in cool place.
Will keep weeks.
Yields 8 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add cake mix, Jell-O, oil and strawberry juice.
Mix well.
Pour into 5 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: *If this isn't a sufficient amount, use extra from a bottle of Ranch dressing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add peanut butter and beat.
Add vanilla.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix.
Make balls, then "x" with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vicki's lasagna
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, pork, onion and garlic.
Drain. Add tomatoes and break up with a fork.
Sti rin tomato sauce, 3 tablespoons parsley flakes, sugar, 2 teaspoons salt and basil. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour or until thick at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour over buttered bread in pan.
Let set awhile before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make lemon sauce (recipe following) and pour over pudding.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with garlic, onions, salt and pepper. Drain grease. Add tomato sauce and chili powder. Heat 9 x 13 pan 5 minutes. Spray with Pam. Take tortillas, scoop meat into tortillas and roll up. Put in pan. Spread chicken soup over top. Pour milk. Cover with cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: candied fruit slices(cookies)
directions: Cream butter; gradually add powdered sugar and cream well. Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in chopped nuts and candied cherries.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Then, divide dough in thirds.
Shape into rolls about 12-inches long. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Cut in slices and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 13 minutes, approximately.

title: garlic grits
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add salt and grits.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 1/2 minutes.
Take off eye.
Add garlic cheese and butter.
Stir.
Pour into baking dish.

title: liver loaf (pork)
directions: Cook pork liver in water to cover for 20 minutes (save liquid).
Grind liver, bacon and onion.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans or 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Mix in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Spread in pans.
Bake 65 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add applesauce and soda.
Beat until light and puffy.
Cream butter and sugar.
Warm the beaten sauce; add the butter mixture and beat until creamy.
Add the cinnamon and spice; thoroughly stir in the flour a little at a time.
Dredge raisins with flour and stir into mixture before pouring into well-greased and paper-lined pans.
Bake in two layers or in loaf at 350°.
Bake until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mexican lasagna(makes 12 servings. prep: 20 minutes)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix chili, cumin, salt, pepper and tomatoes in bowl.
Mix sour cream, scallions and chiles in second bowl.

title: brunswick stew for a crowd
directions: Cook meats and save the broth.
Grind the meats, onions and tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients including broth.
Cook over a low heat, stirring frequently.
The mixture burns easily.

title: sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
When just slightly cool, add sherbet and put in refrigerator until partially set.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs one at at time, beat after each.
Sift together flour, cocoa and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well and pour into a greased 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot relish
directions: Grind apples, tomatoes, green peppers, large onions and hot pepper in a grinder or chopper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Boil 15 minutes.
Put in clean jars and set in hot water to seal.
Great with beans and meats.

title: potato pancakes
directions: In bowl, gently combine potatoes and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and onion.
Stir into potato mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a preheated greased skillet.
Brown lightly on both sides.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Place oats in container of electric blender or food processor; process until finely ground; set aside.
Beat butter in a large bowl at medium speed of an electric mixer; gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine ground oats, flour, soda, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate morsels, grated chocolate and pecans.
Drop dough by level tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool slightly.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: raspberry chicken
directions: Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put pecans in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients on top of pecans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: wassail
directions: Insert cloves in oranges about 1/2-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
At the same time, heat cider in a large kettle on low heat.
Do not boil!
Remove cider from heat; add lemon juice, cinnamon sticks and clove studded oranges.
Cover and heat for 30 minutes on low heat.
Remove from heat and add gin and brandy. Serve warm.

title: trey's favorite stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken in small strips and coat in cornstarch.
Cut all veggies into small pieces or cubes.
Stir-fry coated chicken in light oil until white in color.
Add squash and green pepper, then add onion and mushrooms.
Stir in bamboo shoots and water chestnuts.
Add soy sauce and garlic to taste.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: nantucket blueberry gingerbread
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, ginger, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: potatoes in half shell
directions: Cut baked potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potato; whip until fluffy with remaining ingredients (reserve 1 cup of cheese for tops).
Mound back into shells.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) until cheese melts.

title: apple cream coffeecake
directions: Topping:
Mix nuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup of sugar; set aside.

title: chocolate cluster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Unwrap cookie dough; place in 2-quart batter bowl. Add peanut butter, mixing well. Add remaining ingredients to dough. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart onto
a 15-inch baking dish. Bake for 16 to 18 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in one cup of cherry juice and one cup pineapple juice;
cool.
Add
Cokes,
cherries,
pineapple and pecans.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: japanese chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken breasts for 8 hours or overnight.
Toss with shredded lettuce, almonds, noodles, onions and poppy seed.

title: turkey with mushroom-wine sauce(low-fat)
directions: Broil tenderloins 5 inches from heat for 10 minutes; turn and broil 10 minutes more.
Meanwhile, lightly brown mushrooms in butter.
Combine cornstarch, garlic powder, chicken broth and sherry.
Add to mushrooms and cook on medium, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve over broiled tenderloins and spinach pasta.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Coat a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray. Layer sweet potatoes in dish; sprinkle onion evenly over top. Melt margarine and add milk, salt and pepper; pour evenly over potatoes.
Sprinkle parsley and Parmesan cheese over potatoes. Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Turn heat up to 375°; remove lid and allow cheese to turn light brown before removing from oven.
Serves 6 (1/2 cup servings).
Each serving contains 137 calories, 3.5 g protein, 3 g fat, 2.6 mg chol. and 69 mg sodium.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend oil with eggs.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and salt.
Add to oil mixture. Stir in apples and nuts. Squirt 3 tablespoons lemon juice over the top after putting in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Batter will be very thick.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crab pie
directions: Crush about 16 to 18 Ritz crackers and mix all ingredients together.
Crumble about 4 to 6 more crackers over top and bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: garden casserole
directions: Cut thin slice off Kuta (or eggplant) lengthwise; scoop out seeds.
Bring water to boil in a large saucepan, add Kuta or eggplant; parboil, covered, for 3 minutes.
Lift carefully out of water, drain.
Cool slightly.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, cook until transparent.
Add sliced mushrooms; cook 4 minutes longer.
Stir in meat; brown lightly.
Add sour cream, egg, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook 3 minutes more.
Remove from heat.

Scoop the flesh from Kuta or eggplant, combine with meat mixture, then spoon mixture back into shell, pulling some mushrooms to surface. Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan and paprika; sprinkle over top. Dot with butter. Place in greased baking dish; bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until browned.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: party dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand for a short time.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion and zucchini in margarine until soft.
Place in 4-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dried peach roll
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening and add milk to make a dough.
Roll out on a well floured board or pastry cloth.
Roll dough to 18 inches long and 12-13 inches wide.
Spread sweetened peaches to within 1/2 inch of the edge.
Cut up 1/2 stick of margarine and place on top of peaches.
Roll up 1/2 of dough from one side and then roll up to meet and pinch together.
Seal ends.
Bake until brown in a well greased cobbler pan large enough to hold the sauce.
After it is baked, add 3/4 stick of margarine, 1-1/4 cup sugar,
1-1/4 cup water.
Put back in oven and let boil 8-10 minutes.

title: lemon angel cake
directions: Make custard of egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and lemon rind.
Cook until custard coats spoon.
Add gelatin; cool.
Fold in the egg white-sugar mixture, beaten stiff.
Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces and stir into lemon mixture.
Pour into well buttered angel cake pan; chill overnight.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: chow mein noodle cookies
directions: Mix chocolate and butterscotch pieces in double boiler and melt.
Add noodles and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper. Makes 3 dozen.

title: sweet sour celery
directions: Clean and cut celery stems into bite-size pieces.
Cook until soft; drain.
Mix the sugar, vinegar and water.
Bring to a good boil.
Add cooked celery pieces.
Set aside to cool and the refrigerate.
Keeps well.
Use as a sour side dish for any meal.

title: portuguese bread
directions: Put the sugar, salt and shortening into a bowl and add the boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in the 1 cup warm water.
Add to the sugar-shortening mixture.
Add 3 cups flour and beat smooth.
Add most of the remaining flour gradually. Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, adding any remaining flour.
Grease a bowl with olive oil and place the dough in it.
Cover with a towel and place it in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour. Punch the dough down and divide into halves.
Shape each half into a round loaf and place each into an oiled 8-inch round pan.
Cover again and let rise in a warm, draft-free place until doubled in bulk, about another hour.
Bake in a 400° oven until nicely browned.

title: jewish cake
directions: Mix first six ingredients at high speed for 7 minutes, scraping bowl several times.
In a separate bowl, mix the butter, sugar and cinnamon well.
Pour half the cake mixture into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan and sprinkle 1/2 of the sugar, cinnamon and butter mixture.
Pour the rest of the cake mixture over this and finish up with the rest of the sugar, cinnamon and butter mixture.
