Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Place concentrate in large mixing bowl and beat 30 seconds. Gradually spoon in ice cream and blend.
Fold in whipped topping, whipping until smooth.
Freeze, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours. Store leftover in freezer.

title: mozzarella stuffed mushrooms
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, preheat broiler if necessary. Remove stems from mushrooms. In skillet, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Add mushroom caps and gently toss to coat well.
Place mushroom caps, stem side up, in broiling pan.
Broil 3 minutes.

title: baked tomatoes and cheese
directions: Cut tomatoes in half, crosswise, and place cut side up in baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese, then top with mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered for 20-25 minutes at 350 degrees until cheese is browned and bubbly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Heat iron
skillet with bacon grease (left from cooking the bacon).
Sprinkle
a
pinch of cornmeal in pan until brown (to know when pan is hot).

title: macaroni casserole #2
directions: Cook
macaroni	and drain.
Combine macaroni and next 5 ingredients;
pour into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine
butter
and
cracker
crumbs;
sprinkle over macaroni mixture.
Bake
at	350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings. May be doubled easily.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling, unsalted water; drain.
Toss all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: chew cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 pan.
Mix eggs and brown sugar over low heat just until sugar melts.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans.
Spread in pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots slightly and drain, slice.
Slice onions in rings and separate. Slice green pepper in rings, heat the following thoroughly but do not boil, soup, vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour marinade over vegetables, cover tightly. Refrigerate 24 hours.
This will keep in refrigerator for a long time.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Break cake in pieces.
Mix pudding according to package.
Pour over cake.
Slice strawberries and mix with glaze.
Pour over cake.
Cream the cream cheese; add sugar and vanilla.
Add the Cool Whip and put on strawberries and glaze.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: *Or graham cracker crust.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onions together in pan.	Drain.	Add sugar, vinegar and catsup.
Stir well.
Add beans.
Stir well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Note:
May add to suit taste:
onion, mushrooms and green pepper.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Combine and beat together.
Drop from teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet; spread far apart.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Marinate chicken at least three hours in combination of all remaining ingredients.
Grill chicken over hot coals for six to eight minutes, turning once.
Serve with rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Roll mixture into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Turn on broiler to brown.
Watch carefully to prevent burning.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Melt fat, blend in flour, add onions and peppers.
Cook until tender.
Add garlic, tomatoes, water and seasonings, stirring occasionally on low heat.
Add rice, shrimp, sausage and tomato juice.
If making ahead, add more tomato juice.
Put into greased casserole.	Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Bake 350°, until hot...about 20 minutes.

title: french chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow greased baking dish.
In another bowl, mix other ingredients and spread over chicken.
Bake covered for 1 hour, then uncovered for 30 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: old-fashioned blueberry muffins(makes 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners. In heavy saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients and stir over medium heat until butter melts.
(Cool until just warm to touch.) Beat in eggs.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine soup, mushrooms and rice in a greased crock-pot.
Stir well.
Lay chicken breasts on top of mixture and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover and cook on low setting 4 to 6 hours. Serves 2, 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a medium pan, combine cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine.
Stirring, bring to a boil, over medium-high heat, and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add to macaroni with 1/2 of cheese.
Put on 1/2 of cheese for topping.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 25 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: tuna macaroni bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and turn into greased 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 375° oven until firm and light brown, about 1 hour.
Cut into squares and top each with catsup or chili sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, sift first 6 ingredients.
Add oil and eggs. Beat together well.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Mix in zucchini and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 80 minutes.

title: jean's trifle
directions: Bake cake the night before in a sheet pan.
Prepare Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water and 8 ice cubes; add strawberries.
Let Jell-O mixture partially set.
Prepare vanilla pudding as directed on package.
Let cool to room temperature before layering.
Cake should be sliced into 3 layers.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and sugar; add cooled, melted butter and mix well.
Press onto bottom and sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken with soup and sour cream together and put into a 3-quart casserole.
(I use a large glass cake pan.) Sprinkle with cracker crumbs; pour melted oleo over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: coconut peaks
directions: Mix above ingredients (except chocolate chips). Form into mounds the shape of mountains. Let dry overnight. Dip top portion into melted chocolate to form "snow" on top of peaks.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: In skillet, fry sausage and crumble.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons, to saute onion, green pepper, celery and green chilies. Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 10 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: To layer ingredients in punch bowl:
Cool cake and slice in chunks.
Put 1/4 of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour 1/2 of one box prepared pudding over cake.
Layer 1/2 bananas on top.
Repeat as before.
Add cherry pie filling next.
Top with another 1/4 of cake.
Pour 1/2 of second box of prepared pudding over cake.
Top with 1/2 of crushed pineapple and repeat.
Put strawberries over all and in center of cake topped with whipped topping.
Great for Christmas or holidays.

title: "frozen strawberries aram yesh's way"
directions: In a blender, put strawberries, sugar and egg white.
Blend for several minutes until lightly thickened.
Put strawberry mixture in Cool Whip.
Cover and put in refrigerator.

title: cornmeal scrapple
directions: In a saucepan, combine the cornmeal, sugar, salt and milk. Gradually stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Cook, covered, 10 minutes longer or until very thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat and stir in sausage.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish, combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper. Stir in vegetables and chicken. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Remove dish from oven. Stir. Top with biscuits. Bake 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden. Serves 5.

title: creative dough
directions: Cook all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring real hard, about 4 minutes or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from saucepan and let stand on counter 5 minutes. Knead dough about 30 seconds or until it is smooth and blended. Cool completely.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: husband delight
directions: Brown meat and pour off excess fat.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook and simmer for 15 minutes. Add chopped onions, including green tips.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Add to mixture.
Then add cooked noodles and top with grated cheese.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Coat meat with flour and brown meat.
Add all of the ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sugar cookiesgroves, texas
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together and set aside.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, green peppers and celery.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: pot roast of beef with wine(gedampfter rindsbreten)
directions: Place boneless roast in nonmetal container.
Add 3 cups wine, onions, carrots, garlic, bay leaves, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and parsley.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn meat occasionally. Drain meat; reserve marinade.
Pat meat dry.
Coat meat with mixture of:
1/4 cup flour, salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Arrange in casserole in the following order: onions (cut in rings); potatoes (cut in rings) and pour on top 1 can cream-style corn.
Place sausage patties on top of corn, pour 1/2 can tomato soup on top of sausage.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread(8 servings)
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Preheat the oven to 350°. Sift the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, pumpkin pie spice, salt and baking soda into a medium size bowl.
Beat the sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs into a second medium size bowl until well blended.
Stir in the dry ingredients until well mixed.
Turn into the prepared pan.

title: camp corn pone
directions: In
a
mixing
bowl,
combine first 5 ingredients.
Add approximately 1 cup warm milk or enough to make mush, and stir well.
Now,
add egg and shortening.
Mix and set aside for 30 minutes
so that mixture reaches room temperature.	Thoroughly stir the mixture.

title: chicken kisses
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Drain, set aside to cool.
Combine celery, onions, and cream cheese.
Mix until completely blended. Chop chicken breast into 1/2 inch pieces.
Add chicken to cream cheese mixture.
Blend well.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Brown the sausage, adding the onions and celery when the sausage is half browned.
Add the sausage mixture, the stock and the seasonings to the crumbled cornbread and biscuits and mix well.
Spread out into a 9 x 13 baking dish and bake at 350 until the top is nice and brown and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar, flour and juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into greased 1 quart casserole.

title: apple slices
directions: Mix Crust:
Beat together flour, salt and shortening.
Add to this egg, egg yolk, lemon juice and cold water.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except the margarine until combined.
Shape into 4 patties.
Coat a nonstick skillet with the margarine; add the patties.
Cook over medium-high heat for 7 to 8 minutes, until the patties form a brown crust.
Carefully turn the patties and cook for another 7 to 8 minutes.

title: brown edge cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and flavorings.
Mix salt, soda and cream of tartar to flour; add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet; press down with floured glass, about 1 inch apart.
(Use only a portion of the teaspoon for smaller cookies.)
To flatten, dip cup or glass into flour and press down on raw cookie.
Decorate center of cookies with a cherry, piece of candied fruit or walnut or pecan piece before baking.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, until edge is light brown.
Take off sheet immediately.
Makes approximately 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: ever ready muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Store in covered container. Batter will keep in refrigerator for about 4 weeks.
Bake muffins at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: country style vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until thickened somewhat.
Add vanilla, salt and half and half.
Beat well again.
Pour into 1 gallon ice cream freezer.
Add milk to fill line.
Cover.
Pack freezer in ice and rock salt and turn until very hard to turn, adding ice when necessary.
If using an electric machine, follow manufacturer's directions.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with 3 cups of juice drained from all fruit or orange juice until it thickens.
Cool.
Then mix in all the fruit that has been drained.
Chill.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all but the mushrooms; cook for 5 minutes on medium to medium-high.
Add mushrooms; simmer for 2 minutes.
Put in bowl; cover tightly and chill for several hours or overnight.
Stir a few times.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a food processor.
To serve, mix with hot water to taste.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into a loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Place potatoes and water in pan and cover.
Cook until potatoes are tender, 12 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter; pour over potatoes.
Stir in parsley flakes.
This can also be cooked in the microwave.

title: coffee cake
directions: Soften yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Mix in butter, sugar, salt and milk.
Stir to melt butter and cool.
Stir in some flour, then eggs, softened yeast and raisins.
Add rest of flour and knead 10 minutes.
Let rise and work down.
Let rise and work down again.
Roll out; brush with butter; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Fold one end 1/3 over and fold other end over it.
Put in pan.
Cut halfway through dough with scissors on both sides several times.
Take each section and twist and press down.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.
Make with water and vanilla.

title: chicken piedmantasa
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of wax paper; pound with mallet until flat like a pancake.
Dip pounded chicken in flour-seasoning mixture in plastic bag.
Do not crowd.
Toss until coated.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Brown chicken breasts on each side.
Keep adding butter as needed while browning the chicken.
Do not allow chicken to burn.
In an 11 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish, layer browned chicken pieces.
Add wine and chicken broth to skillet, stirring getting all the goodies left from frying the chicken; pour wine-broth mixture over chicken breasts.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
This dish may be frozen.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with low salt crackers.

title: ann's heavenly hash
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and mix with Dream Whip.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill in bowl or mold.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: In a small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until mixture holds stiff peaks when beater is raised.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and warm water; set aside. Scald milk; stir in margarine and 1/2 cup sugar. Cool to lukewarm. Add eggs, salt and 2 cups flour; beat thoroughly. Add dissolved yeast and remaining flour. Beat 5 minutes. Cover and let set in a warm place to rise until doubled in size.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken; remove.
Simmer 1 quart chicken broth with onion and celery until tender.
Mash onion with a potato masher and remove any large pieces.
Mash celery.
In a separate pan, melt butter and blend in flour.
Add to chicken broth.
Pour the 2 kinds of cream into broth.
Add cooked rice and chicken which has been chopped into tiny pieces.
Season to taste.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
Bake at 400° or 450°.

title: grandma's rice pilaf
directions: Brown 1 pound rice in 1/4 pound margarine.
Add 3 cans beef consomme, 1 can mushroom stems and pieces, salt, curry powder and green onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour at 350°, then use as stuffing for turkey or bake, uncovered, for an additional 30 minutes or until done.

title: orange delight
directions: Place cottage cheese in large bowl.
Fold in dry Jell-O and fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: creamy fruit refresher
directions: Slightly thaw the frozen fruit and orange juice concentrate. In a blender container combine mixed fruit, orange juice concentrate, banana and 1/2 cup cold water.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Transfer the mixture to a 2-quart pitcher.
Stir in the milk.
Serve immediately or chill in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight and stir just before serving.
Garnish each serving with a quartered orange slice, lemon peel twist and mint sprig if desired.
Makes about 6 (12 ounce) servings.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, flour, milk, lemon rind, juice and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 to 50 minutes. Cool.
Yields one 10-inch pie.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, mix flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Mix in flour slowly.
Stir in chips. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Mix all ingredients together; mixing well.

title: maja blanca maiz
directions: Scape corn from cobs and strain through coarse muslin cloth. Add the sugar, rice flour and coconut milk and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly and adding coconut oil little by little to avoid sticking. When thickened, pour into coconut-oil greased platters. Serve with toasted coconut with sugar.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake sweet potatoes at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until done. Remove the skin while the potato is still hot.
Mixer can be used to mix potatoes well with butter, flour, vanilla extract, sugar, spices, salt and milk.
Divide mixture evenly into pie shells. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In bowl, mix the peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
In heavy saucepan, cook sugar and milk until begins to boil. Continue to boil for a full 5 minutes over medium heat.
Stir constantly, then pour over other mixture.
Beat until smooth. Pour into a buttered pan.
Cool completely; cut into squares.

title: mardi gras dessert
directions: Take the 2 cans of pineapple chunks and drain. If there is not enough liquid to make 2 cups, add water to make 2 cups.
Cook juice and vanilla pudding until thick; cool. Add pineapple, bananas, cherries and mandarin oranges. Mix well. Pour into pan or bowl and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate overnight. May add coconut or marshmallows if wanted.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften and mix together good.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.
Double for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple reserving juice in a small saucepan.
Set aside pineapple.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups. Bring to a boil.
Place gelatin in a bowl.
Add boiling liquid and stir to dissolve.
Cool until slightly thickened.
In a bowl, whip cream.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese; blend well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart serving bowl and chill at least 3 hours or overnight. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: macaroni, ham and cheese casserole(great for a chilly night!)
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch dish. Saute onion.
Toss pasta with shredded cheese.
Add onion and cubed ham.
Melt butter; add flour and blend.
Gradually add milk; stir until thickened.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over pasta.
Add buttered bread crumbs last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rum pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk; beat until it thickens.
Fold in whipped cream and rum.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
sprinkle 1/3 cup toasted coconut over the top.

title: sue's taco dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add back to pan.
Add grated cheese over low heat, stirring often.
Add can of drained tomatoes.
Stir until cheese has melted.

title: cheesy meatball patties
directions: In a bowl combine 1/4 cup Prego, beef, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Shape into 4 patties, 1/2-inch thick.

title: broiled salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salmon.
Brush over steaks; marinate for 30 to 45 minutes, refrigerated.
Broil on both sides until lightly browned and tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients in blender.
Pour in heavy saucepan and heat over low heat until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Place pretzels and butter in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Spread cream cheese mixture with lukewarm pretzels in bottom of baking dish.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling pineapple juice; stir in strawberries and allow to thicken to jelled point. Spread over cream cheese and pretzel mixture.
When set, spread the whipped topping on.

title: noodle haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips over low-medium heat on stove (double boiler can be used).
Remove from heat; carefully mix in chow mein noodles.
Fold in peanuts.
Stir carefully until mixture is stiff.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper; cool.

title: indian corn stew
directions: Cook onions, peppers and butter for 5 minutes.
Add meat and allow to brown.
Add corn, soup, sugar, salt and black pepper, simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in flour blended with water.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Delicious with cornbread or main dish.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta. Add onion and cucumbers.

title: macaroni salad or casserole
directions: When the macaroni and cheese dinner is done, add Veg-All, onion, tuna and mayonnaise.
Mix well and either heat in oven a few minutes until warm or chill and serve as either a casserole or salad.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet (iron skillet).
Add brown sugar, then arrange pineapple slices.
Can put cherry in center, if wanted.

title: wassail
directions: Pour apple juice and cranberry juice into large kettle.
Add cinnamon sticks, whole cloves and thinly sliced unpeeled orange. Bring to a boil, then simmer for at least 1 hour.
Serve warm. This can be put in crock-pot and kept on low for continuous serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Fold in dry ingredients and add nuts. Bake in loaf pans for 1 hour at 325° (or until done).

title: lazy mommy dip
directions: Combine sour cream, blue cheese and salt in small mixing bowl. Cover and refrigerate. When ready to serve, garnish with chopped parsley.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin in hot water.
Thaw frozen strawberries in hot gelatin.
(This also quick cools the gelatin.)
Add all ingredients.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture in a 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Freeze about 5 minutes.
Refrigerate remaining half. Spread 1/2 pint sour cream over frozen gelatin mixture.
Add balance of mixture and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill and serve with thinly sliced cucumber or lemon and a dollop of sour cream for garnish.

title: fresh apple crunch
directions: Fill a casserole dish with sliced apples. If very sweet, add the lemon juice.
Add the water, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Crumble the bread over top. Sprinkle the brown sugar over. Dot generously with butter or margarine.
Cook 45 minutes or until apples are tender at 350°.

title: easy stew
directions: In large pot, brown beef in a little water.
Precook hash browns (1/2 package at a time) in microwave for 6 minutes on High power.
In pot with browned meat, add cooked potatoes, drained carrots, 2 cans soup and 1 can of water.
Stir together and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low to medium heat for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring and adding more water as needed.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: corn pudding(servings: 4.  preparation time: 1 hour and 10 minutes.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Place in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for one hour, or until set.

title: cheese spread
directions: Run cheese, green pepper, onion and eggs through a food processor.
Add salt and pepper, horseradish and salad dressing to taste.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, syrup and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cook, stirring constantly until clear and thickened.
Add jello, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Slice berries in pie shell.
Pour in jello mixture.
Chill until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: curried chickpeas and vegetables
directions: Cook chickpeas in enough water to cover until tender, 1/2 to 1 hour.
Saute onion in olive oil.
Add to chickpeas.
Add carrots and zucchini.
Cook on low heat until vegetables are tender.
Add a little water if necessary to keep moist.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons coriander, 1 teaspoon cumin and 1 teaspoon turmeric.
Add salt, depending on your taste.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add fresh coriander leaves, chopped fine, and 1/2 small chili if you like it hot and spicy.
Just before serving, stir in yogurt.

title: golden graham smores
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips to boiling in a large saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over in a large bowl; toss until coated.
Fold in marshmallows 1 cup at a time.
Press in pan with buttered hand.
Cut in squares after letting stand 1 hour.
Store at room temperature.
Yield:
24 two-inch squares.

title: banana-nut bread and cream cheese spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until brown.
Wonderful warm with butter or Cream Cheese Spread.

title: cheese spoon bread
directions: Place milk in top of a double boiler over boiling water; cook until hot.
Stir in cornmeal; cook stirring until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in butter, cheese, yolks and salt.
Stir until cheese melts.
Beat egg whites at room temperature until stiff peaks form; fold into cornmeal mixture.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffed and browned.
Serve immediately.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; add eggs and milk.
Stir in mixed dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in rhubarb.
Batter will be thick.
Spread into a well greased 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: quick chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine cocoa, margarine, milk, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add oatmeal.
Drop on cookie sheet or wax paper and cool.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, bring tomato juice, garlic, 3/4 of the seasonings and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer mixture 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and sift 3 times.
Take about 2 tablespoons flour mixture and sprinkle over nuts and fruit. Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Add applesauce and sweet milk.
Add flour; mix well.
Add fruit mix.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well. Combine flour, salt and soda and add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto nongreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cold dutch indonesian chicken appetizers
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in blender. Add to chicken and mix well. (Add more yogurt if needed to dilute dressing a bit.)

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs. Stir in peanut butter and dry ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and push a Hershey's Kiss in center of cookie. Return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes.
Use a 350° oven.

title: smoked salmon (must prepare ahead)(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Bone and flake salmon.
Mix salmon thoroughly with cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish and liquid smoke.
Place in 3-cup mold or bowl that has been lined with plastic food wrap. Chill 6 hours and unmold onto a plate.
Garnish with thinly sliced lemon.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: curry slices
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cucumbers and onion.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with ice water and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Rinse and drain again.
Combine all ingredients.
Heat just to boiling.
Fill pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Refrigerate when cooled.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: date and nut squares
directions: Mix dates and water in pan.
Cook on stove for 5 minutes or until thick when stirred.
Set aside.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: In a bowl or a bag, combine flour, salt and cayenne pepper. Add chicken pieces and shake to coat.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Toss together bread and pineapple.
Melt margarine; add sugar and eggs.
Beat until well blended and pour over bread and pineapple.
The longer this has to soak the better.
Overnight is best.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until well browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add herbs and chicken and brown.
Mix cream of chicken soup, tomato soup and mushrooms.
Put chicken in casserole dish.
Add soup mixture.
Cover; cook 1 hour at 300°.

title: noodle dough
directions: Mix flour and salt together. Add eggs, oil and water together with flour and salt.
Knead until no longer sticky. Add more flour if needed.
Roll out and cut in fine strips. Dry out on board or table.
Boil water and cook until tender.
Use in soups.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients. Form into balls.
Use a nonstick pan and melt together the chips and paraffin over heat, slowly. Don't boil, just heat.
Take a toothpick and dip the balls into chocolate and put on wax paper.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Melt jelly and mustard in saucepan over low heat.
Cut wieners into 1-inch chunks and add to jelly-mustard mixture.
Heat until warm through and transfer to chafing or warming dish to keep warm.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6.
Delicious with steaks and other meats!

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger
and drain.
Stir in beans and peppers. Fix taco
seasoning
mix
according
to
directions and add to hamburger while it is browning.
This makes a dip.	Layer dip, sour cream, cheeses and olives.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: cappuccino pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to directions on package using milk and coffee granules.
Fold in 1/2 c. prepared whipped topping.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Before serving, top with remaining whipped topping and almonds.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook
chicken;	cut
into
bite size pieces; set aside. Cook noodles
according	to
package
directions.
Set aside. Combine soup
and next 10 ingredients in a 2-quart bowl.
Stir well. Heat, stirring once.
Place 3 noodles in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer half each of chicken pieces and soup
mixture over noodles;
repeat layers.
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbles. May be microwaved.

title: cheddar-dill popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Generously grease 8 medium muffin cups. Beat eggs slightly in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients with fork, just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Fill muffin cup 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes.
Decrease oven temperature to 350°. Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until deep golden brown.
Remove from cups immediately.
Serve hot.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams.
Pour over vegetables in saucepan. Put enough water to cover vegetables.
Simmer on medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Melt butter in large pan.
Add flour and half and half.
Stir with wire whip.
Keep mixing, about 15 minutes, until thick, then add vegetables to it.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix thoroughly with hands.
Shape into balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Flip halfway through baking time to allow even browning.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Add hot water to jello and melt marshmallows in this.
Add other ingredients and let set.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato in jacket until well done.
Peel and add sugar. Mix with potato until it makes a dough.
Roll out on floured surface until thin.
Spread peanut butter on top.
Roll up. Refrigerate; when well chilled, slice.

title: lisa's cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together and set aside.
Mix margarine and sugar together until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla to sugar mixture.
Mix dry ingredients with butter mixture.
Add Rice Krispies, chocolate morsels and raisins. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry sausage, then add cheese; cool.
Add egg.
Stuff mushrooms.
Bake about 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken livers with bacon
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 of onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with the remaining onions; bake for 5 minutes longer.
Extra mushrooms added are great.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Melt oleo and add sugar.
Beat in eggs, milk, cornmeal, vinegar and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into shell and bake at 375° about 20 to 30 minutes.
Pie is done when knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Turn oven off and let pie completely cool in oven (overnight is best).

title: jill's white icing
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff;
add sugar, shortening and vanilla alternately.
Covers one cake.
Very good.

title: jelly roll
directions: Combine salt, eggs and baking powder in bowl.
Place over smaller bowl of hot water and beat with rotary eggbeater, gradually adding sugar until mixture becomes thick and lemon colored.
Remove bowl from hot water.
Fold in flour and vanilla. Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 400° for about 13 minutes.
Turn out on cloth, spread with jelly and roll up.

title: delicious homemade salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs, then add the remaining ingredients.	Heat on medium heat,
stirring constantly until thickens.	This dressing is excellent to use with cabbage slaw.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Jell-O with 3 cups sugar and 3 cups of boiling water until dissolved.
Add 4 cups cooled water and lemonade and mix well. Add extract and pineapple juice.
Freeze overnight.
Take out 1 hour before serving and add ginger ale.
Will be slush form.
This is great!

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: In skillet brown meat.
Drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.

title: pasta a la oleo
directions: Fill medium saucepan 3/4 full of water; bring to boil over medium heat.
Add noodles and continue boiling until tender; drain noodles and place back into pan.
Put in 1/2 to 1 stick butter and toss gently until coated well.
Salt to taste and enjoy.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine fruit, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix in sour cream and sugar.
Stir all ingredients.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately.
Add vanilla.
Put into a greased and floured (deep) cake pan.
Put in cold oven and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: sausage crescent nuggets
directions: Lightly brown sausage and drain well.
Mix cream cheese and sausage until well blended.
Roll out crescent rolls into two rectangles pinching crease together.
Spoon sausage mixture onto dough forming a log roll long wrap of the dough.
Fold dough around log roll.
Brush outer dough with egg white and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool and slice.

title: fanny's french dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly; pour into jar with screw top.
Shake in jar before each serving.
Start with less sugar, add to desired taste.

title: col. harland sanders pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, syrup, sugar, salt, lemon juice and butter. Add vanilla and pecans and mix.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with ice cream.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart baking dish while heating oven to 350°.
Mix in a bowl the flour, sugar, egg, milk and baking powder.
Pour into melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour canned fruit over mixture.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini bread(low-fat, low-sodium)
directions: Lightly oil and flour dust 2 bread pans.
Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry tart
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut Crisco into mixture.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk; mix well.
Take 3/4 dough and pat into greased large cookie sheet.
Spread cherry pie filling over dough.
With remainder of dough, roll thin and cut in strips to make lattice, top with powdered sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate 'n caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and milk; mix well.
Press half of dough evenly in bottom of greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts evenly over dough; drizzle evenly with ice cream topping.
Crumble remaining dough mixture over ice cream topping. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until caramel begins to bubble.
Cool completely and cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: kaffeebrotchen
directions: Bring butter to room temperature.
Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and flour.
Roll out dough 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter and lay on ungreased pans or on waxed paper on breadboard.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Brush with lightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut up small. Roll 15 to 20 minutes until done. Drain. Put in baking pan. Lay cheese on top. Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
If need be, add a little milk to make cheese loose.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend together flour and sugar, then sift into eggs.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Turn into a 9-inch pie plate (greased). Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until coconut is nicely browned.
Makes its own crust.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Uncover.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes (according to your microwave).

title: copper pennies
directions: In a reservable container, layer carrots, bell peppers and onion rings; set aside.
Combine vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard, soup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in a large jar.
Cover container tightly and shake until blended.
Pour over vegetable. Refrigerate overnight.
Tans lightly.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine oats, cocoa and salt.
Combine margarine, sugar and milk; boil for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla; pour over oats mixture. Stir only to blend well; drop onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Add celery and green peppers; let stand 20 minutes longer.
Drain well.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Press broccoli between paper towels to remove excess water. Combine cornbread mix, eggs, onion, cheese, butter and seasoning. Stir well. Stir in broccoli. Batter will be thick. Pour mixture into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly. Cut into squares.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon-colored.
Combine salad oil, sugar, zucchini, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Mix well.
Then add flour and nuts.
Put in well-greased 3-quart Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool for 10 minutes. Store in covered container or wrap in foil.

title: frozen coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in a bowl.
Gradually add milk. Beat until smooth. Stir in vanilla, coconut and Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Freeze about 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with toasted coconut, if desired.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: white butter frosting
directions: Beat butter and Crisco together real good.
Add sugar on low slowly.
Add Pet milk and vanilla.
Whip real good.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Reserve 36 whole almonds; finely chop or grind remainder. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Grease and flour pan or large oblong dish for baking.
Mix sugar and eggs.
Pour in oil, vanilla and anise.
Slowly put in flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour into dish (batter). Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown.

title: mom's b&b pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onions; let stand 3 hours. Drain off accumulated liquid.
Add celery seed, mustard, ginger powder, turmeric, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until mixture is boiling.
Put in sterilized jars and seal while hot.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.
These are very easy to make and delicious!
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: In saucepan combine potatoes, onions and salt.
Add enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook until tender, drain.
Place potatoes in casserole which has been lightly greased.
Sprinkle flour over potatoes.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with grated cheese and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crab and cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Turn soup into saucepan. Stir in milk, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice; heat to simmer. Stir in half of the cheese and drained crab meat.
Mix with hot cooked rice. Turn into shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° about 15 minutes until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted. Serve.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: hot virginia dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with wheat crackers.

title: spicy corn and tomato salad
directions: Combine tomato, corn, peppers, garlic and parsley in medium bowl.
In a small bowl, whisk the oil, dressing and lemon juice. Pour over vegetables and toss.
Marinate for at least 30 minutes. Serve at room temperature or slightly chilled.
Serves 4. Contains 56 calories and 1.7 g fat.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place slices of bread in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle cooked sausage over the bread.
Mix together the milk and eggs.
Pour over sausage and bread.
Top with mushrooms (if desired) and the cheeses.
Cover with plastic wrap and let set in refrigerator overnight so the milk soaks into the bread.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: stir-fried steak
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in skillet.
Add round steak and brown.
Add soy sauce; cook until done.
Serve over rice.

title: mound cake(it tastes like a mounds candy bar)
directions: Bake in a long pan according to cake instruction.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour (sifted), salt and baking powder. Pour into 3 small pans or 2 loaf pans or tube pans, greased and floured.
Bake in cold oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: aunt mattie winn's sour cream cookies(1876 - 1958)
directions: As written by Aunt Mattie Winn.

title: pastry
directions: Place flour in a large bowl. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Cut in cream cheese until mixture forms dough.
Blend in vanilla.
Makes a double crust.

title: turkey minestrone
directions: In a large kettle over medium heat, saute onion in oil until tender, about 4 minutes.
Add the next 6 ingredients; cook until meat is no longer pink.
Add tomatoes, broth, zucchini and mixed vegetables.
Cover and cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Add beans, macaroni, vinegar, salt and pepper; simmer for 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
16 servings (4 quarts).

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes
Remove from oven.
Cool.
Top with fruit, preserves, nuts or just plain.

title: roast beef dinner
directions: Rub roast well with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides. Place in a covered roaster and cook at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours.
The last hour add the potatoes, onions and carrots.
More vegetables may be added if cooking for a crowd.
Green beans are good, too.
Fix your meat and set the timer on your stove; when you come home from work or shopping, put in vegetables.
You can have a good meal with little work.

title: one pan granola
directions: Pour liquid ingredients into a large roasting pan and heat in 250° oven for 10 minutes or until mixture is warm and thinned; stir to blend.
Mix together the dry ingredients except fruit. Remove roasting pan from oven and slowly add dry ingredients to liquid mixture in pan.
Stir until well blended.
Spread evenly in pan and return to oven.
Bake approximately 2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.
Granola should be golden brown.
Remove from oven.
When cool, add fruit, if desired.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: lobster stew
directions: Boil lobsters and remove meat immediately.
Use a heavy kettle and simmer coral, tamale and shells in 1/2 cup butter for 8 minutes.
Remove shells and add meat cut in fairly large pieces. Cook very slowly for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; add very slowly 1 quart of milk, cooking slowly and stirring constantly while adding milk.
Allow stew to stand refrigerated at least 6 hours before cooling or it will spoil.
Reheat but do not boil.

title: brie pastry
directions: Unroll four sections of the crescent rolls.
Pinch together to conceal seams and form a rectangle.
Place the Brie in center of pastry and wrap the pastry around the cheese; pinching seams. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm with crackers.
Serves 8 to 12 persons.

title: el paso casserole(microwave)
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz, soup and milk in a 2 quart mixing bowl until smooth. Then combine all remaining ingredients except corn chips. Place 1/2 the corn chips in bottom of 2 quart baking dish and top with 1/2 Cheez Whiz mixture.
Microwave on high for 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mushroom and clam dip
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter; add remaining ingredients.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: bran muffins by the pail full
directions: Combine All-Bran and salt. Stir in boiling water, then buttermilk. Cool to lukewarm.
In mixing bowl, cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Stir into bran mixture. Combine flour and baking soda. Add 100% bran. Combine well and add all ingredients.
Stir just enough to dampen dry ingredients. Store batter in refrigerator until ready to use. Will keep 4 weeks.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in boiling water for about 3 minutes.
Squash must still be a little crisp.
Drain.
Combine chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in the carrots, squash and onions; add salt to taste.
Combine stuffing mix with the melted butter.
Spread half the stuffing mix in bottom of a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top of stuffing mix, then sprinkle the rest of the stuffing on top of the vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves six.

title: lemon butter chicken breasts
directions: Flatten chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine flour and salt; dredge chicken in mixture.
Liberally sprinkle lemon pepper on each side of chicken breasts.
Saute chicken in melted margarine for approximately 5 minutes on each side or until tender.
Leave chicken in pan and stir in lemon juice.
Increase heat to deglaze pan (approximately 1 minute).

title: chicken tremendous
directions: In bottom of greased baking dish, place onion soup, rice and chicken.
Mix soup with 1 can water.
Place over layers, season to taste.
Bake covered at 350° about 1 hour, until chicken is tender.

title: ho bo bread
directions: Then add 1 cake yeast and 1 unbeaten egg.
Gradually add 2 cups flour.
Beat on #3 speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer and stir in 1 cup flour.
Turn out on floured board and mix until smooth. Cover and let rise in warm place.
Cut rolls and butter.
Put in greased pan.
Let rise again and bake. 425° oven for 20 minutes until done.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Add Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Fold in cookies.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch dish.
This can be frozen.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: In blender, grind cranberries.
Cover with 2 cups sugar and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate peanut butter drops
directions: In large bowl, at low speed, beat 1 tablespoon of water and all ingredients except the chocolate chips until mixed.
Increase the speed and continue beating for 2 minutes.
Stir in chips. Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheets.
Bake in 370° oven for 12 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and blend well.
Add milk to bananas.
Add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: italian pie
directions: Cook vermicelli and drain.
Combine with butter, Parmesan cheese, egg and basil.
Chop all and press into bottom and sides of 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and sausage with onion in skillet.
Drain.
Combine meats and spaghetti sauce in a mixing bowl.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese over crust.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook pudding according to directions (do not use instant). In dish, layer bottom and sides with vanilla wafers (do not crush).
Layer with bananas (sliced).
Layer of pudding.
Continue layering wafers, bananas and pudding until dish is filled. Decorate top with remaining bananas.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer items in large bowl as listed, adding cheese after stirring salad.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking or roasting pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients, except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.
Also terrific with Lipton onion recipe soup mix.

title: fresh vegetable risotto
directions: In a large saucepan, cook mushrooms, onion and garlic in hot oil until onion is tender, but not brown.
Stir in rice.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes.
In another saucepan, bring broth to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer.
Slowly add 1 cup of broth to rice mixture, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook and stir until liquid is absorbed.
Add 1 cup more broth, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring constantly until broth is absorbed.
It should take 15 minutes.
Stir in tomato, carrot and remaining half cup broth. Cook until rice is slightly creamy and just tender, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheeses and basil.
If desired, garnish with tomato slices.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: soft raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
(Do not drain.)
In mixing bowl, cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yield: About 6 dozen cookies.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine Bran Buds and boiling water and let stand 1 hour. Combine all ingredients; add Bran Buds and water mixture last. Bake as many as you like.
Keep batter in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: mexican steak
directions: Puncture both sides of steak.
Put in shallow casserole. Combine beer, red pepper, garlic, cumin and chili powder to form a marinade.
Pour over beef.
Marinate for 1 to 2 hours or longer. Remove from marinade; place on rack of broiler pan.
Season both sides with salt and pepper to taste.
Broil to desired doneness. Time will depend on thickness of steaks.

title: sugar pea casserole
directions: In casserole dish, put 1 can of peas and asparagus, 1/2 can soup and 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Asparagus is in the center of the casserole.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crust and sift crackers.
Add raisins, nuts
and cherries. Mix fruit and vanilla, then milk; mix well.
Press in pan which has been lined with wax paper.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with sugar.
Melt peanut butter and 1 1/2 sticks of margarine together; combine with crumb mixture. Mix well.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; pack well. Melt 1/2 stick margarine and chocolate chips until smooth.
Spread over top of crumb layer.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush approximately 25 to 30 cookies.
Mix with melted butter; press in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pork chop and corn stuffing bake
directions: Combine soup, celery, onion, paprika and stuffing mix and put in greased pie plate.
Arrange chops over stuffing mixture.
Press lightly into stuffing.
Combine sugar and mustard; spread evenly over chops.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: yankee banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening;
add egg yolks.
Mix soda in flour.
Add flour and soda mixture, salt, bananas and pecans to cream mixture.
Fold
in
stiffly
beaten
egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit tea
directions: Brew tea in water.
Add sugar and concentrate.
Stir and chill.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix together brown sugar, margarine and egg until fluffy.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and milk; mix.
Stir in chocolate chips. Spoon into lined cupcake tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes. Makes 1 to 1 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: fajitas(chicken)
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients.
Marinate chicken; cook with onion and green peppers.
Wrap in tortilla and add tomatoes and cheese.

title: shredded carrot salad
directions: Combine raisins and water; let stand 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; toss gently.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: grandma herring's blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients together and add alternately with the milk to the butter and sugar mixture.
Last, add the preserves and stir well.
Bake in 2 layers at 350° until done.

title: orange date-nut bread(yields 1 loaf)
directions: Quarter orange; remove peel.
Scrape white membrane from inside of peel; cut peel in thin strips and chop to make 2/3 cup.
In boiling water, cook peel until tender; drain and dry.
Into mixing bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the peel, dates, sugar and nuts; mix well.
Combine eggs, milk and melted butter or margarine; stir in flour mixture just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; cool before slicing.

title: aunt katie's corned beef pastries(spicy corned beef in an easy sour cream roll pastry)
directions: Cream butter. Add sour cream and salt. Mix well. Gradually stir in flour. Dough will be slightly soft. Roll into a ball and cover with plastic wrap. Chill 4 hours.

title: swedish butter balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and
vanilla
thoroughly.
Add salt to flour (not sifted).
Stir
to
blend.
Add
dry ingredients and nuts to creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls, flatten out with a fork.
Bake on
ungreased
cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll
in powdered sugar while warm.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.
Omit salt if using salted butter.

title: anise-cinnamon dried tea mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove chicken.
Add onions and minced garlic; cook until just tender.
Return chicken to pan.
Combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, oregano, celery seed, bay leaves and hot pepper, if desired.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup Sauterne, if desired.
Cook, uncovered, for about 15 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles or spaghetti.

title: cream cheese filling
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.

title: copeland's easy dinner rolls
directions: Combine the warm water and yeast in a large bowl.
Let the mixture stand until yeast is foamy, about 5 minutes.
Stir in butter, sugar, eggs and salt.
Beat in flour, 1 cup at a time, until dough is too stiff to mix (some flour may not be needed). cover and refrigerate 2 hours or up to 4 days.
Grease a 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Turn the chilled dough out onto a lightly floured board.
Divide dough into 24 equal-size pieces.
Roll each piece into a smooth round ball; place balls in even rows in the prepared pan.
Cover and let dough balls rise until doubled in volume, about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake until rolls are golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush warm rolls with melted butter, if desired. Break rolls apart to serve.

title: chicken orange salad bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Garnish with orange and apple wedges.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage, pepper, onion and celery. Drain and set aside.
In saucepan, combine rice, soup mix and water.
Bring to boil and cook 7 minutes.
Combine sausage mixture, rice mixture and almonds.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hershey's doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar. Beat until well blended. Add melted butter. Stir in morsels and nuts. Pour in pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove and serve warm if desired. Recipe can easily be doubled. Bake two pies, freeze one for later use.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Grate lemon peel and add to creamed mixture.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and milk to creamed mix.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine lemon juice and xxxx sugar; pour over hot loaf.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs and white glaze.
Mix on medium speed.
Add one egg at a time.
When all eggs are added, beat on high speed for one minute.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Yields 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Let stand for one hour before serving.

title: herbed cream cheese appetizers
directions: Thaw pastry sheets at room temperature for about 20 minutes before unfolding. Place each rectangle on lightly floured board. Cut out about 24 (2 1/4-inch) rounds with biscuit cutter.
Prick rounds with fork, then bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: jalapeno cheese pie
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients and
pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed. Cool slightly and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla, then nuts and chocolate.
Spread in greased pan, 10 x 15-inch, and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dog team sticky buns
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Mix in 3 cups flour, plus or minus 1. Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, adding more flour as needed.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out into rectangle and butter well with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar.
Roll into jelly roll. Slice into 1-inch thick pieces.

title: hawaiian sipper
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender or food processor; process 2 minutes. Serve immediately. Yields approximately 1 quart.

title: mom's fruit whip
directions: Beat at room temperature egg white, until foamy.
Add sugar, slowly, and mashed fresh fruit pulp (strawberries, or bananas, or peaches, or raspberries.
Do not use fresh pineapple or kiwi.) Continue beating until a large bowl is almost full of this light, tasty topping for cake servings (instead of frosting).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except crackers.
Put in casserole dish.
Crumble the Ritz crackers on top; drizzle with butter. Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix together Kool-Aid, water, sugar, orange juice and pineapple juice.
When chilled, add ginger ale and soda.

title: ratatouille(pronounced rah-tah-too-ee)
directions: Cut unpeeled eggplant, squash and zucchini into 3/4-inch pieces.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add squash, eggplant, zucchini and onion.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until vegetables are almost tender, stirring frequently.
Add seasonings.
Continue cooking, stirring frequently, 1 minute or until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with tomato.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well and set aside.
Beat eggs; stir in milk, sugar and oil.
Quickly stir egg mixture into dry mixture.
Carefully stir in blueberries. Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Add buttermilk, butter and eggs.
Beat at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Uncover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (or bake immediately at 350° about 30 minutes).

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in two 8-inch pans at 350°.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cook together until thick the pineapple, sugar and flour. Stir as they will scorch.
Bake and cool pie crusts.
Cut up bananas and line pie crusts.
Sprinkle nuts over bananas.
When pineapple mixture has cooled, spread over top of bananas and nuts. Sprinkle coconut over all.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle a few chopped nuts and more coconut over top.

title: lemon lush
directions: Make pudding and refrigerate.
Mix margarine and flour.
Press on bottom of pie pan (can add nuts, if desired).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and cool.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and put into greased casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with potato chips, if desired.

title: mini cheese and onion pastries(taken from a pillsbury cookbook)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine cheese and scallions.
Separate dough into 16 triangles; cut each in half diagonally to make 32 triangles.
Place rounded teaspoonfuls of cheese mixture in center of each triangle.
Bring corners to center over filling, overlapping ends; press gently to seal. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Brush each lightly with oil and sprinkle with dill weed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: kentucky beer cheese
directions: Pour beer into small bowl and let it stand at room temperature for at least one hour. Whisk in spices and let stand for at least 30 minutes.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Stir and cook until mixture is thickened.
Add ham and potatoes.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french toast with bacon
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, with fork, beat eggs and milk until blended.
From French bread, diagonally cut twelve 3/4-inch thick slices; reserve any remaining bread for use another day.
Soak bread slices in beaten egg mixture, turning to coat both sides well until all egg mixture is absorbed.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook bread until browned on both sides, turning once.
Remove French toast to warm platter and keep warm. Repeat with remaining bread slices, adding another tablespoon salad oil to skillet, if necessary.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve with bacon and maple syrup, if you like.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend remaining ingredients
until
crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve plain or with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Wash and prepare the fruit for baking.
Put the fruit in the dish with the butter.
Pour the flour mixture over the fruit.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: ravioli and meatball casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a 2-qt. casserole mix pasta sauce and soup until smooth.
Stir in meatballs and ravioli.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 15-25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts; remove bones. Save broth. Grease a large casserole

dish with butter. Line casserole with stuffing mix, 1/2 of the chicken and the mushroom soup and 1 soup can of the stewing broth. Repeat with stuffing mix, pieces of chicken, cream of chicken soup and 1 can of broth. Sprinkle with stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spicy chocolate pretzels
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt and spices and sift together 3 times.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Beat well.

title: lyndsay's dirt salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix and pineapple with juice in a large bowl; mix well.
Stir in marshmallows and whipped topping.
Spoon into a clean, large flowerpot.
Cover with Oreo cookies that have been crushed.
(I place in a plastic bag and roll rolling pin over cookies to make appearance of dirt.)
Chill until serving time. Place artificial flower in pot just before serving.
Have fun! Serves 12.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in milk, sugar, shortening, salt, egg and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth. Mix in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead until smooth; put in greased bowl.
Turn greased side up, cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down; roll into a rectangle.
Spread with margarine and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up like a jelly roll; cut into slices.
Let rise 40 minutes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: barley oven pilaf
directions: Simmer water, barley and salt for 15 minutes.
Saute onion, carrot and oil.
Add to barley mixture and rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix together crushed pineapple and cut up apples.
Place in covered container and refrigerate.
In saucepan, cook pineapple juice, egg, sugar, cider vinegar and flour until thick.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, fold Cool Whip into cooked mixture.
Then add Spanish peanuts.
Then add apple and pineapple mixture.
Serve.
Makes a good-size bowl.
(Leave peels on apples.)

title: soy sauce
directions: Put oil in a large pan or wok.
Saute scallions, green pepper and mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Add rice (uncooked).
Sprinkle soy sauce over rice mixture until rice is golden brown.
Add 1 can chicken broth.
Cover; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grits bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Place in well-greased muffin pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: rick's chicken tropical
directions: Combine mustard and molasses in small saucepan.
Add other ingredients.
Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Place chicken in flat casserole and pour mixture over it.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato beoreg(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Fry meat until cooked; add onions and parsley.
Cook until onions are soft.
Season meat with salt and allspice.
Peel potatoes.
Cook in salted water until tender; drain.
Mash with butter or margarine.

title: hamburger vegetable main dish casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Place biscuits on cooking sheet and bake for 15 minutes.
Place biscuits on top of casserole and serve.
Time 20 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time.
Combine flour and soda, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in by hand the beaten egg whites.
Pour into three or four 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips, in a 1-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, or until heated through.
Stir in cheese.
Top with potato chips. Cook in microwave on Medium for 2 minutes, or until cheese is softened.
Yields 3 to 3 1/2 cups.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and chocolate chips in a double boiler over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add your nuts and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: swordfish with roasted onion vinaigrette
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine onions, oil and 1 tablespoon thyme in large baking dish.
Bake until onions are golden and tender, stirring occasionally, about 40 minutes.
Stir bell pepper and vinegar into onions.
Season with salt and pepper and push to one side of dish.
Season fish with salt and pepper and arrange alongside vegetables.
Bake until fish is opaque, about 10 minutes.
Transfer fish to platter.
Arrange vegetables over. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and green chilies in butter.
Make sauce by mixing Pet milk, chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and chicken broth. Add sauce to chicken, chilies and onion.

title: monkey bread
directions: In plastic bag or bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cut biscuits into fourths and shake in sugar mixture.
Place in ungreased Bundt pan.
Melt 1 stick of butter with brown sugar, nuts and honey.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into bite size pieces.
Flour and brown beef in hot oil a few pieces at a time.
When all beef is browned, return beef to large Dutch oven or pan.
Add onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour in 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
To make additional gravy, make a paste of 2 tablespoons flour and water.
Add 3/4 cup milk to paste.
Stir and pour over beef, uncover and cook to desired consistency.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: dot's chocolate pies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg yolks, 1/2 cup flour, 1 teaspoon vanilla, cocoa and milk.
Stir well.
Cook until thick on stove or 5 minutes in microwave.
Take out and stir; put back in for 5 more minutes.
Stir well.

title: gladys starr's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat well.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add flour and vanilla to other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oriental hot dish
directions: In 2 tablespoons oil, lightly brown hamburger, celery and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake another 30 minutes longer.
Cover with chow mein noodles and serve.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cut bottom round roast into 1-inch steaks.
Put meat into large cooking bag.
Pour all ingredients on top of meat.
Put a couple of holes in top of cooking bag.
Bake 3 hours at 350°.
Use 2 forks and shred beef in all the juices (it will look like too much sauce but will work into the beef).
Serve on buns with coleslaw.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender; add tomatoes, olives, mushrooms and oregano.
Add ground beef.
Place half of cooked spaghetti in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with half of vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup Cheddar cheese over this.
Repeat layers.
Mix soup and water until smooth.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 12.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix vanilla wafers with butter.

title: cheddar chicken divan
directions: Make a white sauce with the margarine, flour, milk and seasonings.
Add 1 3/4 cups cheese; stir until melted.
Arrange broccoli or asparagus and chicken in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and almonds.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Cut in butter as for regular biscuits.
Stir in starter until well mixed.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead very lightly.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick and cut into small rounds.
Place on buttered baking sheet. Bake in 425° oven for about 10 minutes.
Watch these because they burn quickly.

title: 2 step devil's food cake
directions: Combine cocoa and 4 tablespoons sugar and water in saucepan. Cook over low flame until thick and shining, stirring constantly. Let stand until cold, stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour; measure and add baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well. Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually; cream well until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add cocoa mixture; beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk; beat well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from top of each green pepper; remove stems and seeds.
In saucepan over medium heat, in 1-inch boiling water, heat peppers to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until peppers are tender to crisp.
Drain.
In shallow baking dish, arrange peppers.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, brown meat and cook with chopped peppers and onions until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon mixture into green peppers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
After the first 10 minutes of baking, baste with tomato basting sauce.
Baste after every 10 minutes of baking.
Serves 18.

title: portuguese biscuits
directions: Combine margarine, cream of coconut and anise flavoring.
Beat eggs with sugar and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add baking powder and salt to flour.
Combine with first mixture and mix well.
Roll dough into pencil strips and form into small rings.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 25 dozen.
Store in airtight containers or freeze in Ziploc bags.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: *Or use Jell-O vanilla flavor sugar-free reduced calorie instant pudding and pie filling and Cool Whip lite whipped topping.

title: broccoli salad 2
directions: Mix onions and noodles in large bowl.
Add broccoli mix, sunflower seeds and almonds.
Mix next 6 ingredients in separate bowl.
Pour dressing over broccoli mixture mix well and serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pot, cook onion, garlic and meat until meat is brown; drain off all fat.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve with your favorite pasta.

title: tommy's excellent chocolate adventure
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until completely blended.
Add cornstarch to milk and egg yolks.
Stir until blended.
Add milk mixture to chocolate mixture.
Heat on medium to boiling point and add margarine and vanilla.
Mixture will be a thick pudding.
Pour into a cooked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip, meringue or whipping cream.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Ham or turkey may be substituted for chicken.

title: italian boneless chicken
directions: Combine eggs, Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
