Stir in chicken; mix well with hands and shape into 3/4-inch patties.
In skillet cook patties in margarine over medium heat for 2 or 3 minutes per side or until golden brown; drain.
Arrange in baking pan.
Cook pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients, except for Mozzarella.
Spoon sauce on patties.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella. Bake at 350° uncovered for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: wrapped chicken breast
directions: Cut ham into 1/2-inch wide pieces.
Wrap around chicken; wrap bacon around ham.
Secure with a toothpick.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Pour mixture over chicken in a casserole dish.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix sugar, water and corn syrup in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat (without stirring) until mixture boils.
Cook until mixture will spin a short thread.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Drop quickly by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Do not beat.
Cool and store in covered container.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add other ingredients to yeast and water.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, heat sugar and water until melts.
Cut shortening (Crisco) into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn onto floured board (or cloth).
Knead until smooth. Roll out in rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with cinnamon over apples, then sprinkle apples evenly over dough.
Roll up dough like jellyroll.
Dampen edge of dough with water and seal.
Slice dough into about 16 slices 1/2-inch thick.
Place in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup around rolls.
Looks like too much liquid, crust will absorb.
Cook 55 to 60 minutes.
(Can use other fruit.)

title: little nut rolls(got this from kay newman's 1950 t.v.)
directions: Use your favorite walnut filling in your Little Nut Rolls.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cut up cheese in a large microwave dish and melt.
Add cream of chicken soup and drained sausage to melted cheese.
Serve warm.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over dates and cool.
Add soda.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix dates, creamed mixture and remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Cover in an airtight container.
Refrigerate overnight.
Do not stir again.
Drop in well-greased muffin pan. Cook at 400° for 20 minutes.
Keeps well refrigerated.

title: jello candy
directions: Mix well. Form into balls.
Refrigerate.
May be rolled in red or green sugar.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute
onion
and
ground
meat until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Add chili and seasonings.
On each tortilla, put a small amount
of
meat
mixture,
cheese
and onion. Roll up and place in
baking
dish.
Pour remaining meat sauce on top, more onion and top
with
cheese.
Bake	at 350° until cheese melts or if sauce seems
too dry or there is not enough to cover the tortillas, use a can of El Paso enchilada sauce.

title: chili dip
directions: Add chili sauce to sour cream to taste and color.
Add dry mustard and garlic powder to taste.

title: southern sausage gravy
directions: Cook sausage in large saucepan over medium heat until brown. Stir to crumble.
Drain off fat except for 2 tablespoons.
Stir in flour.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes.
Serve over hot, homemade biscuits.

title: chocolate cake(no fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients until well mixed.
In a medium bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.
(Can dust top with powdered sugar.)

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in fourths.
Roll these in 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Grease Bundt pan and sprinkle some nuts in bottom of pan.
Put in biscuits and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake supreme
directions: Blend cake mix with puddings, oil, eggs and water.
Pour into greased 11 x 14-inch pan.

title: banana split bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar, egg and butter until fluffy.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, mix bananas and milk; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda onto paper plate.
Add dry ingredients to creamed butter mixture alternately with banana mixture, stirring together with a rubber spatula until dry ingredients are blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Drop pan twice from a height of 6 inches to counter, to remove any air bubbles.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Fry onion in butter; stir in soup, water, milk and cheese. Heat until blended.
Add chicken, parsley and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Drain.
Put in casserole bowl.
Pour sauce over half cooked noodles.
Mix well. Sprinkle with cheese; broil until bubbly.

title: crab dip
directions: Shape cream cheese into a circle.
Top with seafood sauce and sprinkle crab on top.
Sprinkle a little garlic powder and parsley on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and cook onion with oregano until tender.
Stir to separate meat; spoon off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until done.
Stir often.
Serve with cheese.
Makes 5 cups.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Place broken pretzels in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; stir in melted margarine and spread mixture evenly in dish. Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool completely.

title: pineapple crunch cake(no eggs!!!!)
directions: Pour pineapple into an 8 x 10 pan.
Cream butter into cake mix. Sprinkle over pineapple.
Bake at 400 degrees until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Let cool.	Whip in eggs until
fluffy
(do not beat too hard).
Top with heavily buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° about 40 minutes.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done. Drain and crumble.
Mix sausage and cheese. Sprinkle sausage and cheese in pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs. Combine and add remaining ingredients (green pepper, onion and light cream).
Pour in shell. Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cocoa clouds
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar and salt until foamy. Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until stiff peaks form. Fold in cocoa.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto brown paper lined cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 275° oven for 20 minutes. Makes 84 cookies, 10 calories each.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, margarine, buttermilk, vanilla and 2/3 can coconut.
Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle rest of coconut on top of pie.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 plastic cups.

title: beef chimichangas
directions: Combine shredded beef, 2/3 cup picante sauce, onion, cumin and oregano in a saucepan and simmer 5 minutes.
Brush outside of tortillas with melted butter and fill inside with beef mixture and cheese and roll up.
Fold ends under and place seam down in a pan. Top with leftover cheese.
Bake 15 minutes in a 475° oven.
Serve with shredded lettuce and picante sauce.

title: apricot bread
directions: Combine flour, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir in flour mixture.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured bread loaf pans.
Bake 1/2 hour in preheated 350° oven, then reduce temperature to 325° and bake for another 1/2 hour.
Let cool in pans for 15 minutes.

title: wheatsworth muffins
directions: Mix thoroughly flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in the butter and fold in beaten egg whites.
Fill well-greased muffin tins 2/3 full of batter.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for about 20 minutes. Makes 24 small or 12 large muffins.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add raisins, applesauce and nuts.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tracey and john's homemade potato soup
directions: You will need a large stockpot.
Slowly heat milk, water, sour cream and butter.
Peel and wash potatoes. Cut into 1-inch cubes. Dice up carrots, onions and celery. Sprinkle in chives.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let cook 2 hours or until all is tender. Best served on a cold Sunday afternoon!

title: scotch cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add raisins which have been cooked, about 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream, eggs and a little milk together.
Then add a little of the wet to the dry and roll out.
Cut with knife.
Continue until all dry ingredients are used.
If you don't think you will have enough wet mixture, add milk.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: pound or plain cake
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream together. Then add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add milk and flour, a little at a time.
Add flavoring.

title: coconut pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Separate eggs, beat whites and put on pie.Cook ingredients until thick; pour into pie crust.
Bake with coconut on top.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop in deep fat, 300°, about half a rounded teaspoonful for each puppy.
They will quickly rise to the top; brown, then flip 'em over.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Wash cauliflower.
Separate head; cook in salted water until done, but not mushy.
Put cauliflower in buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
While cauliflower is cooking, soak white bread (that the brown edges have been trimmed) in 3 cups of milk.
Break up bread after soaking; add onion and celery.
Cook in heavy skillet milk, bread, celery and onion until thick and creamy.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over cauliflower.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream of chicken and mushroom soup
directions: In a pot, heat the butter.
Add mushrooms and saute until tender.
Add the flour and cook for 2 minutes.
Add the chicken, broth, cream, seasonings and parsley.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: gin fizz
directions: Blend with ice in a shaker until smooth.
Yields 1.

title: squash muffins
directions: Combine
margarine,
sugar
and molasses, beating well. Add egg;
beat well. Stir in squash.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add
to
squash
mixture, mixing well.
Stir in pecans. Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: salsa chili
directions: Brown onion and pork in oil in skillet or Dutch oven until pork is no longer pink.
Stir in salsa and beans.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Ladle into bowls and add lettuce, Cheddar cheese, sour cream and green chilies.
Makes 6 (1 1/4-cup) servings.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.
(Can substitute nonfat plain yogurt for mayonnaise.)

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter morsels & chocolate morsels in a heavy sauce pan; cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until morsels melt.
Remove from heat; add peanuts, stirring to coat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool completely & store covered at room temperature.
Yield about 4 dozens.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Chop ham finely.
Chop onion.
You may include tops, if you wish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Line bowl with Saran Wrap; pack cheese mixture into bowl.
Chill overnight.
Turn out onto plate.
Remove Saran Wrap.
Serve garnished as desired.

title: salami
directions: Mix well.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator (mix 3 times during this time).
Shape into loaves.
Bake on broiler pan.
Put meat thermometer in center of a loaf; when it reaches 170°, it is done.
Bake at 250°.

title: chicken and spinach casserole
directions: Mix salt, pepper and garlic powder with thawed chopped spinach.
Spread in greased baking dish.
Lay chicken cutlets on top of spinach.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove foil.
Spread Dijon mustard over chicken.
Lay low-fat Muenster cheese over chicken.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more to melt cheese.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil and spray with Pam.
Arrange crackers in single layer, edges touching. Put butter and sugar in saucepan to boil.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Beat all this together; mix 1 box Jiffy mix.
Add 1/2 pound sugar to Jiffy mix.
Beat in broccoli mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Great and easy.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Chill dough. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cookies do not spread.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: burritos
directions: Saute ground beef and onion together until beef is brown.
Add salt, chili powder and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and refried beans. Simmer for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally so will not stick.
Using a tablespoon, place meat in the middle of a tortilla. Roll up and fry in large frying pan.
Brown on one side and then the other side.
Salt the top side as you take them out.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in oven until time to serve.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
First, the cake pan, prepare it by melting the butter and the brown sugar in it to cover the bottom.
Strain the pineapple; cut them up and scatter the pieces over the bottom of the pan.
Next, a dough:
Beat the eggs with the sugar; mix in the other ingredients.
Put the batter in over the brown sugar and chopped pineapple and let it cook for 1/2 an hour.
It melts in your mouth.

title: soft sugar cakes
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add baking soda and baking powder; add milk and stir.
Then add flour.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet about 4 inches apart.
Sprinkle with sugar or sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes or until light brown.

title: walnut balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except confectioners sugar.
With hand, mix until thoroughly blended.
Refrigerate dough 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 375°.
Form dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets; bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set but not brown.
Let stand 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack; cool partially.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm; cool completely.
Just before serving, re-roll in sugar.
Makes about 20.

title: pecan bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and egg.
Dust pecans with a little flour.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak 2 pounds beans overnight.
Cover with cold water and heat until skins pop.
In beanpot, combine beans with all other ingredients.
Cover with water and cook 7 to 8 hours at 250° to 300°.
Add water every hour and a half or as needed.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine cheese, soup, onion, margarine, 1/4 salt, pepper and sour cream.
Mix well.
Fold in hash browns. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine corn flakes and 1 tablespoon margarine and sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: chocolate sauce for ice cream
directions: Melt candy in a bowl in the microwave with about half of the whipping cream (you don't want the sauce too thin).
Add liqueur to your taste and mix.
Pour over ice cream while warm.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Mix the eggs and milk.
Mix the water and flour.
In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, layer chili peppers, then cheese.
Repeat.
Combine the egg and flour mixtures and pour it over.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Pull out and top with thin layer of tomato sauce and rebake 5 to 10 minutes.

title: annie's dixie dandies
directions: Melt baking chocolate in microwave on low; stirring constantly.
Mix in peanut butter.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until uniform.
Drop by spoonfuls on to wax paper.
Serve when cool.

title: mexican-style cheese strata
directions: Sprinkle the broken tortilla chips evenly over the bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese in a medium bowl; combine with rotary beater the eggs, milk, green chillies, onion, catsup, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Pour over cheese in dish. Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until set and lightly browned. Garnish with whole tortilla chips and halved tomato slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fudge pie
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, heat spread and chocolate until melted and smooth; remove from heat. In small bowl, blend eggs, sugar and flour; stir into chocolate mixture. Pour mixture into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes (center will be soft).
Cool completely.
To serve, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut in slices.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cut the chicken into pieces, and dredge each piece in flour. Brown the pieces in the bacon fat, then pour in 5 cups of boiling water.
Simmer the chicken, uncovered, until the meat falls from the bones.
Drain the broth.
Bone, skin and chop the meat. Reserve the meat and broth only.

title: wikiwiki dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend in 1/4 cup milk.
Add remaining milk, pineapple and pudding and beat only 1 minute.
Put in dish and chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: holiday sweet potatoes southern style
directions: Mix potatoes, butter, grated orange peel, orange juice, syrup and egg yolks.
Stir until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar. Fold into potato mix.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° for 15 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco. Add rest of the ingredients. Start in
a cold oven. Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: stir-n-roll pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Measure all ingredients in bowl and stir vigorously until mixture leaves side of bowl.
Gather dough together and press in a ball.
Knead dough 10 times and divide in half.

title: peanut butter playdough
directions: Mix peanut butter and syrup.
Add powdered milk and 10x sugar to form dough.
If sticky, add more milk powder; if dry, add syrup. Make it at play time and eat it for a snack.
Use marshmallows, raisins, chocolate chips, etc. for decorations.

title: crawfish ole
directions: Layer pepper rings in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine olive oil and garlic; drizzle over pepper rings. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven. Stir salsa into pepper rings. Top with crawfish tails. Sprinkle with lemon rind and Monterey Jack cheese. Return to oven. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Garnish with lemon slices and cilantro sprigs.
Serves 4.

title: microwave fish steamed in lettuce
directions: Line the bottom of a shallow glass dish, large enough to hold fish fillets without overlapping, with lettuce leaves.
Place lemon slices from one lemon on lettuce in a single layer.
Sprinkle fish with minced garlic and season with lemon pepper and salt-free seasoning.
Brush with melted margarine, then put paprika on fillets.
Cover with additional lettuce leaves, so fish is not showing.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine the cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Set aside.
In a bowl, whisk milk and pudding; mix for 2 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Spread over the crust.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with whipped topping and nuts.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add bread crumbs to milk and let stand a few minutes.
Mix with ground beef, egg, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Shape into loaf pan.
Combine catsup, brown sugar, mustard, salt and water.
Pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: raspberry glazed chicken wings
directions: Two hours or day before serving:
In medium bowl combine salt, pepper, jam, mustard, garlic and vinegar.
Whisk until mixed.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Place the oats	in
a
blender container.
Cover; blend for 1 minute until
ground.
In
a
bowl	stir
together oats, flour, sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Combine milk and oil; add to flour mixture.
Stir
until
moistened.
Form
into a ball; flatten slightly with
hands.
Dampen
work surface to prevent sliding. Place ball of dough between two squares waxed paper; roll out dough to fit pie
plate.
Peel
off top paper and fit dough, paper side up,
into
pie
plate.
Remove paper.	Prick bottom and sides, flute
edge.
Bake
in 450° oven 10 minutes. Cool and fill as desired.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Mix the crabmeat, cream cheese, onion and vermouth (optional) together and spread over the bottom of an unbaked pie shell.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze and drain spinach (most of the water needs to be out of thawed spinach).
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours, covered.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Combine with cucumber and onions.
Pour your favorite Italian dressing over vegetables.
Let marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: broccoli dip #1
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water.
Drain.
Saute onion in hot butter; blend together soup, cheese and seasonings over low heat. Cook until cheese is melted.
Add onion and broccoli and cook 1 minute.
Stir in almonds.
Serve hot.

title: "bearly" hot chili
directions: Brown ground beef with the chopped onion.
Drain, rinse and pat dry.
Using large pot, combine soup and water; bring to a boil.
Add drained kidney beans, chili powder, tomato wedges and ground beef.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: red fish creole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until wilted.
Add green peppers, celery, garlic, salt and pepper.
Saute briefly.
Blend in tomatoes, parsley and hot pepper sauce to taste.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes more.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange fish fillets in a large baking dish that has been lightly oiled.
Cover with sauce.
Bake about 15 minutes.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Blend butter, mustard, poppy seed, worcestershire sauce and onion.
Split rolls and spread mixture on each roll.
Put one slice of ham cut to fit on each roll.
Then cheese and another slice of ham.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: fried stuffed jalapenos
directions: Parboil peppers for 2 or 3 minutes, until they are semi-tender.
Cool.
Slit sides of peppers and carefully remove seeds.
Stuff grated cheese (your favorite!) into peppers.
Dip in tempura batter and fry until golden brown.

title: mom willardson's fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit in a large bowl.
If using canned fruit, drain all liquid from fruit before adding to the salad.
Add the sour cream; mix well.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve chilled.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Spread onto a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; remove and set aside. Mix together the remaining 7 ingredients; spread over above mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza salad
directions: Prepare shells according to package and drain.
Mix dressing according to package directions and set aside.
While pasta is still warm, add tomatoes, cheese and onion.
Season with oregano, grated cheese and garlic.
Pour dressing over salad and toss. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pralines (candy)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat to soft ball stage 232° stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat with a wooden spoon just until mixture begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by tbsp. onto greased waxed paper. Let stand until firm.
Yield 2 dozen.

title: mom's earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Spread pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour over pecans and coconut mixture.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Add eggs, buttermilk, oil and pineapple; mix well. Blend in Raisin Bran.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes according to size of muffin tins.
Makes 3 to 5 dozen.
It is better if you mix up batter the night before.
Keeps up to six weeks in refrigerator.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix together and form into walnut size meatballs.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° to 400° until done (8 to 10 minutes).

title: quick-glazed pork burgers
directions: Combine ground pork, water chestnuts, green onions, salt and pepper, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Divide mixture into 4 equal portions and shape into patties about 1/2-inch thick.
Place patties in heavy skillet.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Turn and cook 5 minutes.
Pour off drippings as they accumulate.
Turn patties, brush lightly with glaze and continue cooking 3 minutes or to desired doneness.
Serve on lettuce rafts.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes; cooking time: 13 minutes.

title: wild rice pork chops
directions: Put rice in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 envelope of onion soup mix and 1/2 can of each of the soups over the rice. Place pork chops next and add rest of soups.
Add water.
Top with undrained mushrooms.
Cover.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: home-style scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs, onion, salt and water.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir vegetables in butter 2 minutes.
Pour egg mixture over vegetables. As mixture begins to set at bottom and sides, gently lift cooked portions with spatula so that thin, uncooked portion can flow to bottom.
Avoid constant stirring. Cook until eggs are thickened throughout but still moist, 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: ice creamy jello
directions: Dissolve 1 small lemon jello in 1 c. boiling water.
Stir in 2 c. vanilla ice cream.
When partially set, add 3 sliced bananas, miniature marshmallows, some chopped maraschino cherries, a small can drained, crushed pineapple, pecans.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; blend in flour.
Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken, peas and carrots, seasonings; heat.

title: tenderloin marinade
directions: Remove all fat and membrane from tenderloin; pierce with fork. Add garlic and marinade.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Cook at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: fishing shack chowder
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter.
Add rest of ingredients. Heat.

title: marinated yellow squash
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate.
Lasts up to 5 weeks.

title: cherry cakes(or other fruit)
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add flour and vanilla.
Pour 2/3 of batter into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Pour pie filling over batter.
Dab remaining batter by spoonfuls over filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini. Mix well.
Add flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serves two loaves.

title: dill bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and heat to lukewarm.
Add yeast, soda, dill seed, minced onion, egg and flour.
Combine ingredients and add flour, beating well.
Turn out on floured board and knead. Place in oiled bowl, turning over so all sides are oiled.
Cover with towel.
Let rise (double) about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Knead and form loaf.
Let rise until light, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush top with butter; sprinkle with salt.
Cool 5 minutes in pan.
Turn out on cooling rack.

title: reuben soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually stir in water and bouillon and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Add corned beef, sauerkraut, cream and 1 cup of the cheese. Cook for 30 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring frequently. Ladle into 8 ovenproof bowls. Top each with a slice of bread and put 1/4 cup of the cheese on top of the bread. Place in oven under broiler until the cheese melts and browns ever so lightly.

title: beef tenderloin with marsala wine sauce
directions: Crush fennel seed (I use wax paper and roll with rolling pin).
Bake or grill tenderloin until medium rare.
Meanwhile, prepare sauce.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter and olive oil in skillet; stir in garlic, red pepper flakes and crushed fennel.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add tomato paste; stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Increase heat; add Marsala and red wine.
Cook about 10 minutes until reduced in half.
Add half and half; stir and cook about 10 to 15 minutes, until sauce is thick enough to coat back of spoon. Strain sauce into bowl.
When tenderloin is about half cooked, rub with 1 tablespoon butter and olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Slice tenderloin into 4 serving pieces and pour the sauce over.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat mushroom soup and cream cheese in microwave until soupy (slightly).
Mix gelatine with hot water and blend with soup mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spray mold with Pam.
Pour mixture in mold and refrigerate until fairly firm.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13
x
9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cream 1/2 cup butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Stir in flour, baking
soda,
baking
powder
and
salt alternately with sour cream.
Fold in apples.
Spread batter in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over batter.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Put into loaf pan and cover with 2 strips of bacon, if you want.
Pour over all of it.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken green noodle casserole
directions: Saute the celery, onion and bell pepper in the oleo.
When tender, add the soup and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Cook noodles in chicken stock and add cut up chicken, cheese mixture and 1 can chopped mushroom pieces.

title: company chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in 1/2 cup butter.
Dip chicken in mixture of first 4 ingredients.
Place diced vegetables in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken and cover with sauce.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown the vermicelli in the margarine.
Add the rice and the chicken broth.
Crumble in some parsley flakes.
Salt heavily, cover, bring to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Stir before serving.
(May need to add a little water, as it is simmering, if liquid cooks out.)

title: pecan chews
directions: In a double boiler melt the caramels and heavy cream over hot, not boiling water.
Scatter nuts thickly in the bottom of the pan. Let caramel mixture cook a few minutes, then drop spoonfuls of the caramel partially over the nuts, letting the nuts stick out around the caramel.
Let stand until firm, then cover or dip each piece with chocolate.

title: no-egg ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients
together and place in electric or hand crank freezer.
Add milk to the "fill" line on freezer.
Fresh or frozen fruit
may	be
added
to
make different flavors (1 quart strawberries, 8 to	10
soft
peaches, mashed and 3 to 4 bananas).

title: chocolate oatmeal pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed; blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: chewy cake squares
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cake should "spring back" to touch.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Roll crackers out very fine.
Mix with melted butter and poppy seed.
Cook fryer and cut off bone in fine pieces.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Mix 1/2 of cracker mix in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan. Pour the wet mixture over cracker layer.
Pour chicken on top of wet mixture.
Last put rest of cracker mix on top of chicken layer.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli, cauliflower and cheese bake
directions: Steam the broccoli and cauliflower until just tender.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the cans of mushroom soup in a bowl with 3/4 can milk.
Beat together until creamy; pour over the vegetable mix.
Take a block of Cheddar cheese; grate and put over top of vegetables and soup.
Do not skimp on cheese.
Take the Ritz crackers and crush (not real fine).
Add butter or margarine until damp.
Spread over top of dish.
Cover entirely; bake at 350° until crumb
mixture is golden brown.
Serves 12 to 15.
Freezes well.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half.
Put yolks in bowl; combine with seasoning. Stuff whites with yolk mixture.
Garnish with parsley.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat the egg.
Mix in the peanut butter, honey and milk.
In a medium size bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add the flour mixture to the peanut butter mixture.
Mix until all the dry ingredients have been moistened.
When the dough is smooth and elastic, spoon into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cold salmon
directions: Boil salmon; skin and bone carefully.
Cool in stock.
Serve on a round platter on a bed of crisp lettuce leaves and sliced cucumbers.
Garnish with sliced eggs, tomatoes and parsley. Garnish with mayonnaise; sprinkle with fresh dill and shrimp. Serve extra mayonnaise.
Halibut or trout may be substituted for salmon.

title: cinnamon rolls in a snap
directions: In a bowl, combine biscuit mix and milk.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead 8 - 10 times.
Roll the dough into a 12 inch x 10 inch rectangle.

title: hamburger-baked bean casserole
directions: Cook and brown ground beef until well done.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl and add ground beef.
Pour and spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover top with bacon strips.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, stir together broth, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Stir in onions and cover with lid.
Microwave on High 10 minutes or until boiling, stirring twice during cooking.
With fork, stir broth in swirling motion without stirring.
Slowly pour eggs into swirling broth, then stir just until eggs are set in long strands.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice.
Layer cabbage, meat mixture, salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water and pour over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or cook in crock-pot for 2 hours on high, 4 hours on low.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar and syrup in 1-quart casserole and stir. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well. Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Peanuts will become light brown and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda.
Gently stir until light and foamy.
Quickly, pour into greased cookie sheet.
Cool 1 hour. Break in pieces.
Store in tight container.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Grease a baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine the sweet potatoes, orange juice, milk, vanilla, sugar, salt, 3 tablespoons melted butter and cinnamon. Beat until fluffy and pour into the prepared baking dish.
Mix remaining butter, brown sugar, flour and pecans.
Sprinkle the mixture over the potatoes.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet until crumbly.
Drain.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook until hot and bubbly.
Garnish with cheese, black olives and onion.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa, then add to creamed mixture.
Add salt and flour alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend in soda and vinegar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 2 (8-inch) round pans.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add oil and the next 4 ingredients.
Beat 6 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a 10-cup greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Drizzle with lemon glaze and cool completely.

title: caramel kisses
directions: Slowly cook sugar, corn syrup, butter and light cream together until 250° is reached on candy thermometer or until a firm ball can be formed when a drop is placed in a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cut into small squares when cool.
Wrap individually in wax paper.
Yield: about 36 Kisses.

title: caramels
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan; set aside.
Melt butter in 3-quart pan.
Add sugar and salt; stir.
Stir in corn syrup.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Use candy thermometer.
Cook and stir over medium heat to 240°.
Remove from heat.
Pour into buttered pan; cool and cut.

title: indian muffins
directions: Mix the egg, milk and shortening together.
Combine with sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased muffin pan for about 20 minutes.

title: low-fat honey-lemon cake
directions: Coat a loaf pan with cooking spray.
Dust pan with 1 teaspoon flour; set aside.
Combine remaining 1 3/4 cups flour and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine milk and next 4 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well.
Add to flour mixture and beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.

title: helen's from scratch pancake mix
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Beat the eggs with a fork.
Add milk, Wesson oil and lemon extract.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until mixed.
Cook pancakes on a heated, greased frypan or grill until covered with bubbles.
Turn pancakes and brown the other side.
Makes 12.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into balls.
Put 1/4 stick margarine in skillet.
Brown meatballs in 3 beef bouillon cubes dissolved in 3 cups hot water.
Put meatballs in casserole dish. Brown 3 tablespoons flour in skillet with leftover fat; add liquid and pour over meatballs.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: green punch
directions: Mix jello, sugar and hot water.
Add juices and blend. Freeze.

title: martha's special pecans
directions: Beat egg whites and water until frothy; add nuts and mix together.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon and toss with the pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread evenly on a cookie sheet sprayed lightly with Pam.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Turn occasionally. Cool; keep in airtight containers.
A great gift.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in 1 gallon jar.
Add salt and alum; fill jar with vinegar.
Put lid on and let set for 6 weeks.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Pour 1/2 of cooked syrups over egg whites that have been beaten. Continue beating while cooking rest of syrup to hard ball stage. Pour over whites.
Continue beating until very stiff and loses its gloss.
Pat out on pastry cloth that has been sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Have a jar of peanut butter soft in pan of hot water.
Spread quickly over candy mixture.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Slice.

title: angel food cake
directions: Bake half of the recipe for Angel Food Cake in a shallow pan (10 x 15-inch), lined with wax paper, in a moderately slow oven (325°) for 20 minutes.
Turn onto a damp cloth or paper sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove bottom paper quickly; cut off thin strips from the sides and ends of cake.
Spread with jam, jelly or whipped cream.
Roll.
Wrap in cloth or wax paper until serving time.
Work quickly or cake will crack.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 8-inch greased pan.
Mix the other ingredients together; will become crumbly.
Cover apples with mixture.
Pack. Place chunks of butter evenly on topping; sprinkle coating of granulated sugar over top.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes in oblong cake pan.

title: gary dean's favorite casserole
directions: In a small skillet, saute onion; set aside.
In a large pan, crumble and brown hamburger meat.
When well done, add salt, pepper, onion and 1 can of soup.
Heat until very warm.
Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise into thin strips.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, oil and nuts.
Beat.
Stir in strawberries.
Batter is thick.
Place in 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Refrigerate.
You can freeze the bread.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg.
Add flour gradually to mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with almonds.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add corn.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to mixture.
Add seasonings and fry in deep hot fat.
Use a small spoon to drop batter.
Serve with jelly or honey.

title: spaghetti in italian fisherman sauce
directions: In large kettle, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender. Add pasta sauce and zucchini.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes. Stir.
Serve over hot spaghetti with Parmesan cheese.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the margarine in casserole dish in the oven. Combine flour, sugar and milk in medium bowl.
Pour the peaches into hot casserole dish, then add flour mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Return to oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: apricot delight
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat until Jell-O dissolves and mixture boils.
Beat together cream cheese and yogurt.
Fold in baby food, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Jell-O mixture.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans.
Combine red beans, celery, green pepper, onions and garlic in a large pot.
Cover with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours until beans are tender and have a thick gravy.
Add pepper, parsley and salt.
Cook sausage according to package directions, cutting into serving pieces.
Put rice over beans and add sausage.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops on both sides in electric skillet.
Add consomme, water and rice.
Season with salt and pepper; add onion slices. Bring to boil; reduce to simmer for about 45 minutes in electric skillet, or bake, covered, in oven at 400°.
Add more water if it dries too quickly.

title: *caramel pecan buns
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar, salt, 2 tablespoons margarine, egg and 2 cups flour. Beat until smooth.
Work in remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Place in a greased bowl; also grease dough.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight or up to 4 or 5 days.

title: herbed chicken pie
directions: Place flour in saucepan and stir in milk slowly.
Add the soup and mix well.
Add chicken, vegetables, onion, salt, butter and heat to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Sprinkle with Thyme and cover with top pie crust. Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 30-40 minutes or until brown.
Will boil out in oven.

title: soupy pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops on oblong baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave 70% for 30 minutes.

title: rolled sugar cookies(mother's)
directions: Beat together lard, sugar and eggs.
Add 1 cup milk and about half the flour that baking powder, soda and salt have been added to.
Mix real well, then add rest of flour.
Add flour to make dough stiff enough to roll out and cut with any size cookie cutters.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with white sugar or colored sugars before you bake.
Makes around 4 dozen medium size cookies.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini with coarse chopper or grinder. Add salt, let stand overnight, if longer than 12 hours refrigerate. Wash and drain well. Add vinegar, sugar. red pepper, turmeric, and celery seed and dry mustard, pimentos, green peppers. Cook in large pot. Bring to boil, simmer for 5 minutes. Makes 5 quarts.

title: lemon pudding dessert
directions: In a bowl, cut butter into the flour until crumbly. Press into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until set. Cool on a wire rack.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut and clean peppers; drop in pot of salted boiling water. Turn off heat and let stand about 5 minutes. Drain. Saut onions in butter. Mix onions, ground beef, rice, salt and 1 can of tomatoes. Fill peppers with the mixture. Arrange in a baking dish; pour 2 cans of tomatoes over peppers and 1/2 cup of water. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; sprinkle tops of peppers with cheese, if desired, and continue baking for 20 more minutes.

title: handy oatmeal cookie mix
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together 3 times. Cut in shortening until mixture has consistency of corn meal.
Add rolled oats and mix well.
Store in a covered container at room temperature.
Makes about 22 cups.

title: southern sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain, peel and cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Preheat oven to 375°. Grease well a 2-quart casserole dish.
Peel bananas and cut into 1/4-inch thick slices. Toss with orange juice and set aside.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Add spaghetti sauce to ground beef.
Simmer.
Cook noodles. Grate cheeses.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
When layering, use sauce, noodles and cheeses.
Cook at 350° until light brown.

title: pepperoni zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine zucchini, onion, cheeses, pepperoni and spices.
Mix thoroughly and set aside.
In another bowl, combine oil, eggs and Bisquick.
Mix well.
Add to zucchini mixture and blend thoroughly.

title: low-fat chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, apple and onions.
In blender, mix cottage cheese and milk.
Whip for 2 minutes.
Add chicken mixture. Season with pepper.
Mix well.
Serve over lettuce leaves or as sandwich filling.

title: honey bun cake with glaze
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put half of the batter in pan (9 x 13-inch). Sprinkle cinnamon mixture on top.
Put rest of batter on top. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry puff delight
directions: Follow jello recipe on box.
Chill until almost congealed. Break angel food cake into chunks and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine Jell-O, strawberries, pecans and Cool Whip. Pour over cake chunks.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Scrub potatoes well; prick with fork. Bake for 40 to 60 minutes, or until cooked through.
Split potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp; reserve shells. Mash potato pulp in bowl.
Add butter, sour cream and enough milk to make of desired consistency.
Mixture should be medium stiff. Add cheese, chives, salt and pepper.
Spoon into potato shells. Arrange potatoes in shallow pan.
Top with crumbled bacon; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in Dutch oven and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in soups, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In food processor bowl with metal blade or blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover.
Process 30 seconds.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: crescent roll pastry
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with vegetable spray.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla together in electric mixer until well blended.
Place 1 package crescent rolls on bottom of pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Place the package of crescent rolls on top of cream cheese mixture.
Brush top with egg white.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: pecan raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease muffin tin. Blend biscuit mix, milk, raisins and vanilla. Stir well.
Melt margarine. Add margarine, pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon to batter and blend well.
If hand mixing, stir at least 30 strokes. Spoon into prepared muffin tin and bake for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, sour cream, lime juice and grated lime rind.
Stir well.
Pour filling into a graham cracker crust. Refrigerate until firm.
Stir sour cream with sugar.
Carefully spread over top of pie filling.
Chill.

title: creole seafood gumbo
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, saute green pepper, onion, celery and garlic in oil until tender, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until fish is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl combine bran flakes and milk.
Let stand a couple of minutes to soften.
Add beaten egg and oil and mix well. Stir together other ingredients in another bowl, add to cereal mixture.
Stir only until combined.
Bake at 400° in lightly greased muffin pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: taco dip
directions: Saute ground beef and onion.
Add taco seasoning.
Add water. Cook 5 minutes.
Add refried beans and mushroom soup.
Cook 10 minutes; put in oblong baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: zucchini lemon bars
directions: In a medium bowl, combine eggs, sugar, oil, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Beat until well blended.
Add zucchini.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir into zucchini mixture and then fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool in pan.
Frost with glaze, if desired.

title: noodle surprise
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and add eggs, milk, salt, butter, green pepper and onion.
Bake in oiled ring mold at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from mold.
Saute onions, celery, mushrooms and choplets, then add mushroom soup and water. When hot, add soy sauce to taste.
Serve over noodle ring.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in pineapple with juice. Sift together flour, soda, nutmeg, salt and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece into a ball. Roll each ball in butter, roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar. Place 3 balls in each greased muffin cup.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until browned.

title: fruit bowl
directions: First, drain pineapple juice into a bowl separate from other and set aside. Cut bananas into slices. Put into a large bowl and mix well!

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a pan and cook for 10 minutes. Cook the rest of ingredients 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine 1 tablespoon melted butter and juice of 1 lemon or lemon extract; add a little milk.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together. Serve on crackers or with vegetables.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix bananas and eggs in a bowl.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add to the first mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Stir well.
Stir in melted butter.
Put in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon baking soda over 1 cup chopped dates. Cover with 1 cup boiling water and set aside.
Mix together 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Add nuts, egg and salt and mix well.
Add flour and mix.
Add date mixture and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and cool, then slice onion. Mix vinegar, oil, salt, pepper, mustard, sugar and tomato soup. Add to carrots and onions.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped apples and chopped nuts.
Pour in greased and floured cake pan or tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in crabmeat, cheeses and onion.
Spoon into a baked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm in center.
I double the ingredients and bake in a 10-inch pie shell.
I like mine very full.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Early in the day:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Into large bowl, measure all ingredients except chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix with spoon.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pannu kakku
directions: Melt butter in pan in oven (9 x 13-inch).
Break eggs into bowl and beat well.
Beat in sugar.
Add milk alternately with flour and salt.
Last add melted butter.
Pour into hot pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar before removing. Serve with syrup.

title: barbecued hamburger sloppy joes
directions: Brown onions and green peppers in oil.
Add meat and brown. Add ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Simmer for 5 or 10 minutes.
Serve on hamburger roll. Serves 6.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa; add 1/4 cup milk, margarine and vanilla.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute; set aside to cool.
In mixing bowl, mix pudding and 3 cups milk.
Beat until thick.
Add Cool Whip.

title: sesame-lime marinade
directions: In a large bowl or plastic bag combine lime peel, lime juice, vegetable oil, sesame oil and salt.
Add chicken to marinade. Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or longer if desired, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Reserve 1/4 cup marinade.
In a small bowl, combine 1/4 cup marinade, honey and sesame seed.
Grill or broil chicken with marinade-honey mixture several times while cooking.

title: fruit 'n' spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer
bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients gradually with creamed mixture.
Stir in mincemeat, nuts, and orange rind.
Drop by spoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Frost and garnish if desired.

title: curry dip
directions: Soften cream
cheese;
spread on the bottom of a plate. Spread seafood
cocktail	sauce evenly over the cream cheese. Cover the sauce
with
well drained crab meat.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Simmer rice, water and salt in covered stockpot for 7 minutes. Add milk and butter and bring to boil. Cook on low in covered pot for 1 1/4 hours (watch carefully; can cook over). Stir frequently. Add eggs, sugar and vanilla (mixed together). Cook
on low until thick.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Let sausage come to room temperature.
Heat oven to 325°. With hands, combine sausage and cheese together in a bowl.
Add Bisquick and blend in thoroughly.
Roll into little marble-size balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 30 minutes. Serve hot or cold.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: naney's divinity
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large saucepan. Cook to 260° (hard-boil) and cool. In mixer bowl, beat 3 egg whites until stiff. Slowly add hot syrup; add vanilla. Add pecans. Beat until dull. Spread on wax paper.
Cool and cut.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Put ingredients into greased baking pan.
Place bacon on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: one-step yogurt pound cake
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend at low speed, then beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tom and jerry batter
directions: Whip the egg yolks until lemon colored and stiff. Add 3 cups powdered sugar and blend well. Add the vanilla and nutmeg. Set aside.

title: banana split pie
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt margarine and add graham cracker crumbs. Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients to form meatballs, or you can use frozen ones.
Bake on a large baking sheet at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: german sour cream pie
directions: Make flaky pie crust for 13 x 9 cake pan.
Peel apples and mix with 3/4 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Place dough in pan and fill to top with apples.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat butter and sugar on low until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press in center and place drained cherry in center.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, eggs, and oil together 2 minutes on low.
Add carrots and walnuts. Mix on high for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes.

title: egg salad spread
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a mixing bowl; season with salt and pepper.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and chill.

title: vegetable casserole(serves 6)
directions: Cook cauliflower and broccoli according to package directions. Drain; cut up any large pieces.
Combine cream-style corn, drained whole kernel corn, cheese and soup.
Fold in cooked vegetables and mushrooms.
Turn mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease oblong pan.
Pour pineapple evenly into pan.
Spoon in pie filling.
Crumble cake mix evenly over this.
Place sliced oleo over mixture and top with nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse in cool water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in a bowl (looks nice in a clear glass bowl).
Combine mayo and sour cream; spread over salad, sealing it.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Place the chicken breasts in a heavy pot with a lid on it. Mix the Coca-Cola and ketchup together and pour on top of the chicken.
Cook slowly until chicken is done on top of stove.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream cheeses and marshmallow cream together until well blended.
Add Cool Whip.
Serve with any variety of cut up fruit.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and tear in small strips.
Mix the next five ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Top with crackers mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes(crock-pot)
directions: Mix milk, cornstarch, salt and cheese together and cook over a low burner until cheese is melted.
Spray crock-pot with Pam. Fill crock-pot 1/3 full of sliced potatoes; add 1/3 sauce. Continue layering potatoes and cheese sauce.
The last layer should be cheese sauce.

title: mother's pimiento cheese spread
directions: Grind sharp Cheddar cheese, Velveeta cheese, sweet gherkins and pimientos together. Add sugar, pepper and Miracle Whip.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Stir mayonnaise into above mixture; refrigerate for 12 to 18 hours.

title: black bean and rice bake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Heat	oil
in
heavy,
large, nonstick
skillet
over
medium
heat.
Add
onion and garlic; saute 8
to 10 minutes until tender.
Add bell pepper; saute 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, lime juice, chili powder and salt; bring to
a boil.
In a 2-quart casserole, mix beans and rice. Pour in
tomato
mixture and stir to combine.
Sprinkle casserole with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until hot and bubbly. Healthy. Makes 4 servings.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, eggs, nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fritos salad
directions: Cook hamburger meat until done; drain off excess grease and add taco seasoning and tomato sauce to the meat.
Cook until it has cooked down a little.
Cut up lettuce and tomatoes in a large bowl.
Add cheese, olives, onion and Fritos.
Pour hamburger mixture over salad and toss.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Prepare creamed potatoes.
Brown and drain ground chuck.
In large covered casserole, put 1/2 of ground chuck, spread 2 cans of vegetable soup over meat and add 2 cups creamed potatoes and spread smooth.
Cover with half of cheese slices.
Repeat each layer.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy mandarin muffins
directions: Drain mandarin oranges thoroughly and cut into pieces.

In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, nutmeg, salt and allspice. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk and egg. Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Gently stir in oranges.
Line egg and muffin pan with paper liners. Fill cups 1/2
full of batter.
Microwave approximately 3 minutes on High or until muffins test done with toothpick.
Remove from
pan immediately.
Makes 12.

title: polvorones(tea cakes)
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill for 2 hours.
Make 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° on greased cookie sheet for 16 to 20 minutes. Roll in additional confectioners sugar and let cool.

title: yellow ring pound cake
directions: Soften margarine.
Add powdered sugar and eggs, then vanilla and flour.
Cook in a tube pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: coconut pie without crust
directions: Mix well the eggs, sugar, melted margarine, flour, milk, grated coconut and vanilla. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer above ingredients in order.
Seal in a Tupperware bowl. Do not mix.
Put in the refrigerator overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend peanut butter and butter.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat eggs and vanilla into creamed mixture.
Form into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain juice from berries and pineapple.
Reserve 1 cup of juice.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of boiling water, then add fruit juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add fruits and nuts. Chill until firm.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake only to heat.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Set aside.
Pour 1/2 cake in pan.
Add cream cheese mixture on top of cake.
Add rest of cake.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix dry jello into Cool Whip and cottage cheese and fruit. Chill.

title: applesauce beef loaf
directions: Blend thoroughly; shape into a round loaf in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
With spoon, make a crater depression in top of loaf.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat in melted chocolate and butter.
Mix in flour mixture and vanilla.
Bake in greased 8 x 11-inch pan in oven at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: You will also need a 12 x 8 pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt oleo. Beat eggs and mix all ingredients together. Place in well-greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: double chocolate fantasy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
In a bowl, combine butter and cookie crumbs.
Press mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Combine the M&M's semi-sweet chocolate mini baking bits, coconut and nuts.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over condensed milk. Press in lightly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cool completely before cutting.
Store in a tightly covered container. Makes 32 bars.

title: chicken and dumplings dinner
directions: Cook fryer in 2 quarts salted water until tender.
Cool, debone and skin fryer and return meat to the broth.
Add mixed vegetables.
Bring to a slow, rolling boil.
Add tortillas, broken into cracker-size pieces.
Cook until dumplings (tortilla pieces) are slightly opaque and tender, stirring to prevent sticking or lumping together.
Don't overcook, dumplings will become tough. Add black pepper to taste.
Serve while hot.

title: lemon onions
directions: Halve the onions and steam until tender.
Place in pan.
Pour the remaining ingredients over the onions.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Broil until slightly brown and warm.
Serves 4.

title: italian pinwheels
directions: Layer circles of hard salami, Mozzarella cheese, Prosciutto, Provolone cheese and Genoa salami.
Cut into 1-inch wide strips. Roll up and fasten with a fancy toothpick.

title: perfect oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, water, raisins, margarine, cinnamon, nutmeg, nuts and salt for 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, oats and soda.
Drop by spoonfuls on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° or until a nice shade of brown.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients at high speed for 10 minutes.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and nuts.
Mix.

title: chicken curry
directions: Place the garlic, ginger, turmeric, cumin, chili pepper, coriander and yogurt in a large bowl with salt to taste.
Mix well.
Add chicken and leave for 4 hours; turn occasionally. Heat the oil in the pan; add the onion and fry until golden. Add the chicken and marinade.
Bring to simmering point; cover and cook for about 30 minutes, until the chicken is tender.

title: chili enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir beef and 2 tablespoons onion until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in chili, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover, simmer 10 minutes.

title: white chili (chicken)
directions: Combine stock, beans, half the chopped onion, garlic and salt. Bring to a boil; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add more stock, if needed.
Saute the remaining onion in the oil.
Add chilies and spices.
Stir and cook briefly, then add to bean mixture.
Add chicken.
Heat through.
Before serving, add the grated cheese. Yield: 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Blend all ingredients with an electric mixer.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Steam vegetables.
Stew chicken and cut into bite-size pieces. Mix vegetables and chicken in a casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Butter the stuffing mix and put on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Set oven for hot (400°).
Cream the shortening.
Add sugar gradually, creaming thoroughly.
Beat eggs.
Add.
Mix and sift 1 2/3 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Mix blueberries with remaining flour; stir lightly.
Bake in greased muffin pans 1/2 hour.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: salsa
directions: Combine ingredients in food processor and process until very fine.
You may alter ingredient amounts to fit your taste.
If you like a chunkier salsa, reserve half of tomatoes and add them at the end of processing.

title: chocolate-raspberry truffle cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, butter and 1/2 cup sugar; blend well. Press on bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Melt butter or margarine with garlic.
Brown chicken.
Puree tomatoes.
Add Italian seasonings.
Put chicken in baking dish. Cover with tomato sauce.
Put 1 slice of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gently mix in with Marshmallow Creme. Add lemon, orange or vanilla to taste if desired.
Serve in bowl as dip for fruit.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Layer as follows:
first layer, line casserole dish with 1/3 crackers (this varies some); second layer, 1/2 the oysters; third layer, crackers and fourth layer, remaining oysters.
Top with crackers and add milk and butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
(Can omit salt, if desired.)

title: mrs. harvey's white fruit cake
directions: Chop nuts and fruit into medium size pieces; dredge with 1/4 cup of the flour.
Cream the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs; blend well.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder together.
Fold into egg and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; mix well.
Add fruits and nuts; blend well.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Line with heavy brown paper bag; grease again.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Place in cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cool in pan on cake rack.
Makes 5 pounds of cake.

title: decorative bread dough
directions: Mix ingredients and knead about 20 minutes, or until of desired consistency.
Dough can be used in any creative way. Baskets may be made by weaving dough on back side of Pyrex baking dish.
To make ornaments, roll dough and cut out shapes with cookie cutters. Prick to prevent air bubbles.
Dampen to make pieces stick together.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.
Paint with acrylic paint, if desired.
Varnish and dry.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine ingredients until crumbly; put mixture in 8 x 12 pan and bake for 15 minutes at 300° until it looks done. Cool.

title: quick and easy chocolate mousse
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend this mixture at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into dessert dishes and chill.

title: marg's strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and soda.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add eggs and oil.
Using a slotted spoon, dip out strawberries from their juice and add to batter, mixing just until combined.
Add enough juice to make nice batter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.
Enjoy!

title: coconut-ice cream dessert
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs; stir in melted margarine.
Put half of the crumbs in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save half for topping.
Mix milk and pudding and add slightly softened ice cream and Cool Whip; mix thoroughly.
Pour on top of crumbs, then sprinkle remaining crumbs over the top.
Store in freezer.
Thaw slightly for 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: apricot-pineapple salad
directions: Drain and chill apricots and pineapples, dicing apricots and reserving juices.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 1 cup reserved juice, save rest for topping.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch shallow dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread with topping.

title: chess cake
directions: Beat
together the cake mix, butter and one egg.
Press into a 13
x
9-inch
buttered
pan.
Mix
cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar
together
and pour over the pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Grease and line
(with wax paper) bottoms only of three 8-inch round layer cake pans.
Set aside.

title: mini pizza
directions: Spoon sauce over muffin halves.
Add toppings.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve shortening, sugar and salt in boiling water; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add to lukewarm mixture.
Sift flour; add to liquids.
Knead well.
Cover with wet towel in warm place; let rise until double.
Punch down; turn on floured board and knead well.
Make 2 balls.
Form into loaves. Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Gradually add milk, egg yolks, lemon rind and lemon juice, stirring until smoothly blended. Add margarine and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour into bowl and cover with waxed paper or plastic film.
Chill.
Fold in sour cream. Turn into baked pastry shells. Serve at once or chill until serving time.
If desired, garnish with lemon slices.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Layer in dish, pie filling, crushed pineapple and sprinkle cake mix.
Cut margarine in slices over mixture.
Add pecans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough on a pizza pan and bake for 8 minutes; let cool.

title: cavatene (dinner)
directions: On high heat, brown the ground beef; drain meat.
Stir in cream cheese.
Turn heat down.
Pour in spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Boil noodles.

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large port add olive oil, garlic and parsley; simmer for a few minutes.
Add beef or pork and sausage meat, cook until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to a simmer.
Cook, uncovered, 2 hours.
Remove carrot before serving.

title: football spiral
directions: Brown ground beef and season to taste with salt and pepper. Drain well.
Add beans and mix.
Add milk and catsup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with thinly sliced onion and then bacon strips.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 450° until bacon is done (about 30 minutes).

title: triple cheese pastrami pizza(yields 16 slices)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place bread, cut side up, on cookie sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and spread with pizza sauce.
Layer pastrami, combined giardiniera and olives.
Top with cheeses.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Cut each half of bread into 8 pieces. Serve immediately.

title: cranberry-peach pie
directions: Wash and stem cranberries.
Mix with peaches.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Toss together with fruit.
Put into crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix butter with stuffing mix and set aside.
Slice carrots and cook until almost done.
Drain.
Saute onion in melted butter.
Add flour, salt, dry mustard, celery salt and milk.
Cook, stirring until thickened.

title: pear pie
directions: Place pears in pie shell.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and rind. Sift together sugar, flour, coriander, nutmeg and salt.
Sift over pears.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover with vented crust. Bake at 4525° until center is lightly browned and pears soft (about 35 to 45 minutes).
Serve with heavy cream while hot.

title: chimichurri argentino
directions: Put all ingredients into a bottle and marinate at least 24 hours.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat
eggs
minutes.
Gradually
add sugar.	Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice; set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.	Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Spread
towel
on
counter
and
sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Turn
cake	out
onto
towel
and
roll up.
Let cool. Unroll and mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on cake and roll up. Slice and serve.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Melt oleo. Add cola.
Heat to boiling point. Cool slightly.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Stir until blended. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in marshmallows.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn muffin frank casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and brown lightly.
Blend in flour, salt and mustard.
Slowly add milk.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add franks and peas.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix together corn oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, pumpkin, chopped nuts and raisins.
Bake in three (1 pound) coffee cans, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Delicious served with cream cheese-pineapple spread.

title: berry delight
directions: Combine graham crackers, sugar and butter. Press in pan and chill for 15 minutes. Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over crust. Top with sliced strawberries. Prepare 2 vanilla instant pudding using 3 cups milk. Pour over strawberries. Chill several hours. Top with Cool Whip and sliced strawberries.

title: fresh flowers
directions: Take 1 roll of fiber paper towels (Bounty).
Cut in half, making 2 short rolls.
(One roll makes 2 rolls of wipes.) Remove cardboard tube.
Place in choice of the Tupperware go-between pitcher, square modular #3, Signature Series #3 or just a plastic shortening can.

title: elegant shrimp saute
directions: Lightly toss shrimp in flour and saute in butter 2 to 3 minutes.
Add onions; saute one minute longer.
Remove from pan. Add wine and boil until sauce thickens.
Return shrimp to pan. Add salt, pepper and lemon juice and cook 1 to 2 minutes longer. Serve over rice.
Broiled tomatoes and steamed broccoli make colorful accompaniments.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli and pat dry with paper towel.
Combine with all other ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers. Great!

title: oyster soup
directions: Put milk into double boiler.
