Rub together the cornstarch and margarine and stir into the hot milk, adding the bacon and celery. Let come to a boil.
Pour a few drops of lemon juice over the oysters and bring them to a boiling point in their own liquor. Drain and (if they should curdle, wash them in a little cold water).
Turn at once into the milk.
Season with salt and pepper; remove the bacon and celery.
Pour over broken crackers into a hot tureen or soup plates and serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: genuine italian pizza dough
directions: Put hot water and oil in large bowl, then add yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add flour slowly to make paste, then a soft dough.
Dough should be oily.
Use well-greased hands to pan dough.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix stirred eggs and sugar well.
Add oil and apples.
Mix well.
Mix flour, soda, spices and salt and add to above.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake in 8 x 10 Pyrex pan (lightly floured after greasing).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese and chili cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add corn and chilies; mix well.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Turn into baking pan.
Bake for 40 minutes or until golden on top and well done. Cut into squares and serve hot with butter or chili.

title: cauliflower and broccoli crunch
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon bits. Toss well. Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Cover and chill for 4 hours. Serves 10 or more people.

title: homemade granola crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.

Lightly grease a jelly roll pan. Combine oats, coconut, pecans, sunflower seeds, wheat germ, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl. Stir together oil, water, honey and vanilla in small bowl. Pour over the oat mixture and mix well.

title: chocolate chip cookie dough cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter; press firmly over the bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of a 9-inch cheesecake pan with removable rim.
Bake at 350° until slightly darker, about 8 minutes.

title: frosted fruit jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello; cool.
Add soda.
Chill until partially set. Drain pineapple (reserve juice).
Fold in pineapple and sliced bananas.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch glass pan and set until firm.

title: stuffed prunes
directions: No need to soak prunes.
Empty into saucepan with water to cover.
Bring to a boil, then cool.
Mix together the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Slit prunes; fill with cream cheese mixture. Chill.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as instructed on box.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients; add to macaroni.
Bake until cheese is melted and bubbly, about 30 to 35 minutes, in 350° oven.

title: open-face beef sandwiches
directions: In toaster or under broiler, toast bread.
Cut bread slices in half and arrange on microwave-safe roasting rack.
Divide beef into 8 portion servings and layer beef on toast halves.
Let stand while preparing sauce.

title: derby breakfast yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm buttermilk; set aside.
Sift soda, salt, sugar and flour into a bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture.
Stir until blended.
Knead and roll 1/2-inch thick. Cut.
Dip in melted butter.
Place in greased pan; let rise 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: cornmeal dumplings with turnip greens
directions: While turnip greens are in their first hour of cooking, prepare dumplings.
Sift and measure cornmeal; combine with other dry ingredients.
Sprinkle onions over this and add enough boiling water to make a moderately stiff dough.
Add melted shortening. Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Shape into small, flat pones.
Add chicken stock to simmering turnip greens at end of first hour, then lay dumplings on top of greens.
Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and mix well.
Put on stove and boil only one minute.
Remove from fire and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well working as quickly as possible.
Drop on wax paper in spoonfuls and flatten in shape of cookie.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil in large pan. Boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Add peanut butter.
When peanut butter is mixed, add oats and walnuts.
Mix well.
Spoon out on foil or wax paper and let cool.

title: juicy tater burgers
directions: Stir onions into milk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine with ground beef and potato flakes.
Mix well.
Form 4 hamburger patties.
Brush Worcestershire sauce over top of hamburgers.

title: apple butter fried pies
directions: Mix flour with enough water to make ball about the size of a golf ball.
On a floured board or paper, roll out the dough, but not real thin.
Place your apple butter in center and bring half of dough over the apple butter.
Press together and fry slowly in small amount of oil.
Brown both sides, you may need a little more oil for other side.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in hot fat until golden.
Add meat and seasonings; brown.
Add drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Cream 3/4 cup
sugar
and
margarine.
Sift
flour
and 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa.	Add
to
creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into
lightly
greased 9-inch round cake pan. Combine sugars and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake
30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
When done turn cake upside down while hot.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter with cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until thoroughly blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, with portions of flour, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla flavorings.
Spoon into a tube pan; bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Mix marinade; add meat.
Refrigerate 8 hours.
Grill 6 inches from coals 35 minutes.

title: corned beef roll-ups
directions: Put corned beef and cheese through food chopper.
Mix in other ingredients thoroughly.
Add enough mayonnaise so mixture will spread easily.
Remove crusts from bread and cut in halves. Spread mixture on bread and roll.
Toast in hot oven.

title: broccoli-stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brush the skins of potatoes with butter and score them down the middle lengthwise.
Bake them for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: hawaiian beets
directions: Drain beets and pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and vinegar and salt.
Cook until thick.
Fold in beets and pineapple.

title: honey carrots
directions: Place all ingredients in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: double apple salad
directions: Cut apple rings into halves. Arrange with fresh apple pieces on salad greens. Sprinkle with celery.
Serve with mayonnaise. Makes 6 servings.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat ingredients with an electric mixer until blended.
Serve with fruit.

title: "un-fried" french fries(one of oprah winfrey's favorite recipes)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice potatoes lengthwise to make "French Fries".

title: breakfast take alongs
directions: Beat together until well blended the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add the combined flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, cheese, wheat germ and bacon.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire cooling rack.
Store in loosely covered container. Yield:
about 3 dozen cookies.

title: banana cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into a large bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping the bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping occasionally.
Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake.
Cool completely before filling with frosting.
Frost with Sour Cream Filling.

title: coconut pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil and pumpkin and beat lightly. Add dry ingredients, including the pudding mix. Blend. Then stir in the nuts. Pour into 2 greased 9 x 4 x 2-inch bread pans and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: triple chocolate mess(crock-pot)
directions: Spray crock-pot with nonstick spray.
Mix all ingredients until smooth. Pour into crock.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Serve in a bowl with vanilla ice cream.

title: christmas wreaths (microwave)
directions: Melt butter with marshmallows.
Tint very dark green with food coloring.
Add vanilla.
Stir in corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Put 2 to 3 cinnamon candies on each wreath.
Chill to set.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Good on graham crackers or sandwich.

title: mexican dip(quick)
directions: Place cheese in shallow serving dish. Pour picante sauce over. Set dish in center of platter and surround with chips.

title: cheesy spaghetti bake
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Break spaghetti in quarters and cook according to directions.
Rinse and drain.
Mix cooked spaghetti and sauce.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add evaporated milk and water.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.

title: bean casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole bowl, uncovered. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients until well blended.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: cold oven butter pound cake
directions: Cream sugar with butter and shortening well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add (flour and baking powder combined) flour mixture and milk alternately.
Beat well after each addition.
Add flavoring.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Put in cold oven and turn oven on to 300° for 90 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich filling
directions: Combine corned beef, cheese, sauerkraut, mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Cover
and	store
in
refrigerator.
To serve, spread filling
between rye bread slices;	butter outsides of bread and cook
on
sandwich grill until cheese melts.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm bread crumbs over top; salt and pepper to taste.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Add pepper, onion, salt, pepper and grated cheese on top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for over 20 minutes.

title: pickled beets and onions
directions: Drain beans and layer with onions in a bowl.
In a saucepan, combine vinegar, water, sugar, oil, salt and pepper; bring to a rolling boil, stirring to keep sugar from burning.
Pour hot liquid over beans and onions.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to marinate.

title: raisin muffin
directions: Baking time: 15 to 20 minutes.
Temperature: 425°.
Size pan: muffin pan.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
Cut in margarine.
Pat down 1/2 mixture in square pan.
Put in a can of cherry pie filling.
Put other 1/2 of mixture on top and pat down. Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: keiv chicken(russia)
directions: Preheat oven to 375F.
In a 2 quart saucepan, melt butter. In a small pie pan, combine bread crumbs, parmesan cheese, basil, and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Dip chicken breast in melted butter then roll into bread crumbs to coat.
Place chicken in a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake for 50-60 minutes or until done.
While chicken is baking, add wine, onion, and parsley to remaining melted butter.
When chicken is golden brown, pour butter sauce over and around chicken.
Return to oven, bake for 5 minutes more or until sauce is hot.
Serve with wild rice.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain.
Add onion, pepper, Ro-Tel and relish.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add cheese and simmer, stirring until cheese is melted.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Pour over hot dogs.
Cook in slow oven, covered, for several hours.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake very well. It is delicious on garden salads.

title: christmas strawberries
directions: Let cool in refrigerator and then form, with buttered hands, like strawberries and roll in red sugar.
Dip tops in green sugar. Can use a sliced almond for stem.

title: quick beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onions in drippings until tender, but not brown. Add with crumbled bacon to remaining ingredients and mix well. Simmer until heated.

title: mexican cheese tortilla appetizers
directions: On cookie sheet, ungreased, spread cheese evenly over tortillas, leaving small margin around edges.
Top with chiles. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: cherry walnut squares
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Stir together the egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Quickly stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Add walnuts.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. (Cookies should be soft in center when taken from the oven.) Cool in pan.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing. Place half of it in 2-quart baking dish. Add chicken. Mix 1 cup broth with each can of soup. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with remaining stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta pedro
directions: Melt margarine, picante sauce and Parmesan cheese until hot. Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Salt optional.
Mix well and pour over pasta and serve.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Cook noodles and cool.
Add everything to casserole and heat for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: split pea soup
directions: Boil peas for 2 minutes; remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Rinse well.
Add to peas, ham, onion, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 1 hour or until done.
Cut ham from bone and simmer until vegetables are done (45 minutes).

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Let orange juice and margarine warm to room temperature.
Mix with 1 box confectioners sugar.
Add crushed vanilla wafers and broken nuts.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: bloody mary
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a blender thoroughly.
Pour vodka into 4 tall glasses in equal amounts. Divide tomato juice mixture equally among the glasses and stir well. Garnish each glass with a celery stick.

title: nacho-style dip
directions: Mix all together and put in crock pot to keep warm.

title: pesto sauce
directions: In food processor, put basil leaves, pine nuts, garlic, salt, cheese and drizzle some olive oil on top.
Put on lid and turn on. Put the remainder of the oil through the hole in lid.
Leave on until well blended.
Toss with hot, cooked pasta.

title: crock pot shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp and rice; place in crock pot.
Cook 6 to 8 hours on low or 3 to 4 hours on high.
Add shrimp last hour of cooking.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: wyoming chili
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Return to soup pot and add chili powder, onion, garlic, cumin, oregano and salt.
Stir to combine.

title: play dough
directions: Mix salt, flour and cream of tartar, then add water, vegetable oil and color.
Cook over medium heat until thick and it feels good.
Stir well while cooking.
Let cool about 5 minutes.

title: meat balls(appetizers)
directions: Mix first nine ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat balls.
Remove and pour off fat.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, confectioners sugar, margarine and vanilla. Form into small balls.
Chill 3 hours on cookie sheet.
Melt in double boiler the chips and wax.
Put toothpick in peanut butter and dip in chocolate.
Return to cookie sheet and cool.

title: apricot bars
directions: Put apricots, pears and juice in a saucepan.
Cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Place in a blender or food processor and process until pureed.
Set aside.

title: cheese squares
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 9-inch baking dish (spray dish with Pam).
Be sure that the center is "set".
Cut in 2-inch squares when slightly cooled.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Cut beef into bite-sized cubes.
In a large skillet heat half of the butter.
Add the mushrooms and brown very lightly.
Remove and set aside.
Add the remaining butter to the pan and brown the onions.
Remove and set aside.
Add the beef cubes to the pan in batches, browning on all sides.
Remove cubes as done, and continue until all beef has been browned.
Remove all beef cubes and set aside.
To the remaining fat in the pan stir the flour, then add the bouillon, wine, and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil and stir until thickened.
Add garlic, salt, thyme, bay leaf and pepper.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press
firmly
into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: savory lima bean scallop
directions: Soak the beans in cold water overnight.
Drain and cover with boiling water.
Add the sliced onion and cook slowly until tender. Drain.
Add salt, celery, green pepper, tomato soup, melted butter, pepper and salt to taste.
Pour into a greased baking dish; sprinkle the top with crumbs and bake in a hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Bacon may be added, if desired, with other ingredients.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: *Nutmeg and ginger are good, also.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Rinse pork chops and pat dry.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Coat with flour.
Brown on both sides in oil in skillet; drain well.
Arrange in single layer in rectangular baking dish. Combine sour cream, soup, soup mix and wine in bowl.
Mix well. Spoon over pork chops.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve with wild rice and julienned carrots.
Yields 8 servings.

title: aunt clara's meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, cracker crumbs, eggs, onion, green pepper, salt, sage,
pepper
and
milk.
Mix lightly but well. Shape into a
12-inch
loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana fudge-walnut brownies
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate chips over low heat, stirring constantly.
Beat in with spoon flour, sugar, walnuts, banana, vanilla, baking powder, salt and egg.
Spread evenly in 8-inch square pan which has been greased only on bottom.
Bake about 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 2 teaspoons mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Grind vegetables.
Sprinkle salt; allow to stand overnight. Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Heat to boiling; simmer for 3 minutes.
Seal in jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Combine cut up cooked beef roast and sauce.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
I also use round steak.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream together cream cheese, egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy.
Remove crust from bread; roll with rolling pin.
Spread cream mixture on bread with medium thickness and roll up.
Melt margarine in separate pan.
Mix 2 cups sugar and cinnamon in another pan.
Dip roll in margarine and then roll in cinnamon mixture.
Freeze overnight.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: boiled bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon slowly in frying pan.
In a saucepan put sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Mix thoroughly.
Add beaten egg and vinegar, mixing well.
Lastly add cream, bacon and fat.
Cook to desired thickness.

title: poppy seed ham rolls
directions: Melt margarine and blend in rest of ingredients.
Split horizontally two packages of Pepperidge Farm rolls without separating.
Spread bottom halves with sauce.
Divide 1 pound of boiled ham between rolls and top with 1 package of Swiss cheese. Replace tops of rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy, 5 minutes on high, scraping bowl occasionally.
Blend in cooled chocolate.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to mixture alternately with ice water, beating well after each addition.
Bake in two lined and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tests done.

title: moist pan dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Combine into bread mixture.
Add seasonings and eggs.
Add enough broth to moisten.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in lightly greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs and mix well. Add the baking powder, salt, vanilla and milk and gradually add flour. Mix well. Add chocolate chips and mix well. Drop on a plain cookie sheet, one teaspoon at a time. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water and blend.
Blend in sugar.
Pour into mold and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold prior to serving. This may also be served with whipped cream.

title: beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket roast with celery salt, garlic salt and liquid smoke.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Combine catsup, vinegar, sugar, 1 tablespoon liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over brisket.
Seal foil.
Bake in oven at 250° for 5 to 5 1/2 hours.
Allow to cool, then slice.

title: the best applesauce cake ever
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, soda and spices.
Add alternately with applesauce and syrup.
Then add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° in a prepared tube pan for 60 minutes or until a toothpick tests clean.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat pineapple with sugar.
Soften gelatin in water and add to pineapple.
Add lemon and cherry juices. Cool mixture.
Mash cream cheese. Add cherries. Add whipping cream. Blend mixture with pineapple mixture.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Heat oil.
Add garlic and ginger.
Stir-fry 15 seconds. Remove garlic.
Add vegetables and soy sauce.
Stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes, stirring vegetables until they are tender-crisp.

title: vegetable and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in large pan and saute onions.
Add mushrooms, rice, soup and Cheez Whiz and stir well. Add frozen broccoli and cauliflower. Blend well. Put in casserole dish. Bake uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in Corning Ware dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in same dish.
Add crushed pineapple.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: aunt lila's wheat germ brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate; cool slightly.
Then add to eggs and sugar and mix well.
Add rest of dry ingredients; then add vanilla and nuts.
Mix until just moistened.
Bake until just done to assure chewiness and moistness (350° for 25 to 30 minutes).

title: gourmet crock-pot chicken
directions: Salt, pepper and paprika chicken breasts; place in bottom of crock-pot.
Mix soup, sour cream and wine; pour over chicken. Sprinkle again with paprika.
Cover; cook on low 7 or 8 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: molasses ginger sugar cookies
directions: In food processor, place flour, baking soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon, mace and cloves.
Pulse 4 to 5 times to sift.
Remove sifted ingredients to sheet of waxed paper.
Do not wash processor.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add baking soda.
Pour mixture over popped popcorn.

title: orange zucchini bread
directions: Mix like you would any other bread.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done. Cool in pans.

title: lynn's company breakfast
directions: Melt butter
in
a large skillet.
Shred dried beef and brown. Add
potatoes
and brown.
Scramble eggs with milk and pour over potatoes.
Add
Cheddar
cheese after eggs begin to gel.
Cook eggs to desired consistency.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream flour, butter and powdered sugar. Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash; add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Slice carrots 1/8-inch thick.
Boil until tender, then cool. Blend remaining ingredients together and add cooked carrots.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring water and 1 cup sugar to boil in large saucepan. Gradually add cornstarch dissolved in 3 tablespoons water.
Stir constantly until thick and clear.
Add few drops red food coloring.
Remove from heat.
Add salt and strawberries.
Cool slightly.
Put in pie shell and refrigerate until set.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Combine first four ingredients and form into 3 - 4-inch balls. Roll in nuts.
Delicious with crackers.

title: game meat
directions: Melt 1/4 pound of butter or margarine.
Add a dash of allspice, nutmeg, cinnamon, paprika and 1 or 2 bay leaves.
Take cut-up pieces in strips of meat and lay in butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Turn heat low and simmer for 10 minutes.
Turn meat and simmer again.
Take a cup of red wine or cream sherry and a cup of water and add to meat.
Dice a small onion in liquid.
Add mushrooms and some parsley.
Keep heat on low so it doesn't get dry.
Add 1 can tomato soup and one can water and simmer slowly until meat is done (10 minutes).
Serve over rice.

title: date balls
directions: Cut dates in half if you do not have the chopped.
Melt dates, margarine and sugar.
When dissolved, cook 8 minutes on low heat.
Remove from stove.
Add other ingredients.
When mixture is cooked, roll into balls and then roll in powdered sugar.

title: quickie chicken l'orange
directions: Preheat oven to 325° (165°C).
Put chicken pieces in a baking dish.
Combine the other ingredients in a small bowl and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: In a
large
mixer bowl, beat margarine until soft. Add sugar and vanilla. Beat until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Beat in flour and cocoa. Add pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: jam bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in egg and lemon rind.
Press half of mixture into bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread with preserves.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: german cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over very low heat, stirring constantly. Cool. Cream remaining butter with cream cheese until softened. Gradually add 1/4 c. sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks, one at a time. Sift flour, soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt 3 times.
Add alternately with sour cream.
When thoroughly mixed, add vanilla and lemon juice.
Fold in egg whites plus 1/4 teaspoon salt which have previously been beaten stiff. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: keebler 15-minutes chocolate-banana cream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine pie filling mix, whipped topping mix, milk and vanilla on low speed of electric mixer until blended. Increase speed and beat until very thick, about 3 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of mixture into crust.
Layer slices of banana on top, reserve 1/2 banana for garnish.
Pour remaining filling into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with sliced banana and additional whipped topping, if desired.

title: sausage-egg bake
directions: Combine sausage and mushrooms in large skillet after cooking sausage.
Saute mushrooms until tender.
Place bread cubes in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sausage and mushroom mixture and Cheddar cheese.

title: red raspberry cream salad
directions: Drain thawed raspberries.
Add water to make 2 1/3 cups liquid. In medium saucepan, heat to boiling.
Pour boiling liquid over gelatin into large mixing bowl.
Add ice cream.
Stir until melted. Stir in lemonade.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in drained raspberries and pecans.
Pour into oiled 6-cup mold.

title: soft pretzels(snack)
directions: Mix yeast in warm water; stir in salt and sugar.
Add 4 cups flour; mix well.
Turn the dough onto a floured surface to knead for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pull off walnut-sized chunks and roll into snakes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
To make shiny pretzels, beat an egg and brush onto pretzels.
Sprinkle lightly with salt. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add green pepper and onion.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients (mustard, ketchup, salt and pepper).
Simmer mixture 10 minutes to warm thoroughly.
Add small amounts of sugar to mixture (about 1 teaspoon at a time, mixing thoroughly).
Taste; add sugar until desired taste is achieved.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients with the broccoli and add the Italian dressing.
Let stand overnight.

title: peanut butter cluster
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter together in medium size saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated. Drop by level measuring tablespoon onto buttered baking sheet. Chill until firm.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread blueberries on top.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Pour melted margarine on top, then nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: roberta's vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables (carrots, tomatoes, cucumbers, mushrooms, etc.).

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour crushed pineapple over top of pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top of the first 2 ingredients.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over the pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until an inserted fork comes out clean.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef in a large skillet until color disappears.
Add onion, green pepper, tomatoes, parsley, ketchup and steak sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and mix with beef mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add soup and mix lightly.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat n' potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9-inch pie plate, combine all ingredients except potatoes and cheese.
Pat mixture along bottom and sides.
Bake 20 minutes.
Meanwhile mix potatoes with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Remove pie plate from oven and drain any excess liquid.
Increase oven temperature to 450°.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top of layer of potatoes on top of meat. Bake about 15 minutes or until heated through and potatoes are golden.

title: cream cheese chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Press one roll of cookie dough in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Beat softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Spread over cookie dough.
Slice second roll of dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Cover cream cheese with slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit surprise pie
directions: Slice the strawberries and combine them with sugar, cornstarch and red food coloring (if desired). Mix well. In a medium saucepan, cook the strawberry mixture over medium heat until thickened. Set aside to cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add spices to the flour and fold in apples and pecans.
Bake in tube pan (greased).
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with half of crushed Oreo cookies. Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Let cool.
Stir together the sugar and egg whites, and add jello along with the Dream Whip. Pour over crushed Oreos and put remaining Oreos over top.

title: raspberry frost sodas
directions: Pour 1/4 cup cranberry juice in each of 24 short wide glasses. Place 1 scoop (about 1/2 cup) sherbet in each glass.
Fill with ginger ale.

title: great baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and pour off majority of grease.
In same pan, brown hamburger.
While doing the above, saut the onion and green pepper in butter, until the onions are translucent.
In a large bowl, mix all of the ingredients (including the pineapple juice) until everything is well mixed.
Bake at 300 for 2 hours.

title: cream cheese cherry sugar-free pie
directions: Melt butter and add to flour; add nuts and press into an 8 x 11 1/2-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until crust is brown.

title: oriental hot dish
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
In frying pan, fry hamburger.
When done, drain.
Add vegetables.
Cook them with hamburger until tender (with lid on pan).
Add cream of mushroom soup, bean sprouts and La Choy sauce.
Cook until hot.
Serve over rice.

title: egg custard
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Put blender on highest speed for 3 minutes.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: hearty salmon pie
directions: Melt margarine; stir in crumbs, 2/3 cup milk, 1 egg, onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in salmon and hard-cooked eggs.
Turn into 9-inch pie plate.
Combine potatoes and 3 tablespoons milk. Beat in remaining egg and 1 teaspoon salt.
Spoon around edge of pie.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake by package directions.
Fill paper cups in muffin pans, 2/3 full.
Cream cheese with sugar and beat in egg and salt. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop one rounded teaspoon cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as package directs.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; gradually beat in well beaten eggs. Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Beat in salad dressing.
Toss together remaining ingredients.
Pour on dressing.
Toss gently.
Adjust seasoning, if necessary.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and bring to boil.
Let cool.
Add topping and buttermilk.
Stir all together.
Refrigerate.
Very easy to make and has a very unique flavor.

title: picante sauce
directions: Scald, peel and chop tomatoes; add all other ingredients and cook about 25 minutes (until thick enough) and place filled jars in boiling water bath canner and boil for 10 minutes.
Makes 12 (1/2 pints).
Add peppers to taste while cooking, for desired heat.

title: ginger glazed carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots in enough water to cover with 1 teaspoon salt until tender. Drain and set aside.
Melt butter and slowly stir in sugar, remaining salt, nutmeg and ginger.
Stir until sugar dissolves and turns golden.
Place cooled carrots in a buttered baking dish and cover with sugar mixture. Bake for 15 minutes in a preheated oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion until done.
Drain well. Stir in spaghetti sauce and ketchup. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: rocky road squares
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips with Eagle Brand milk and butter.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, mix nuts and marshmallows; fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Chill 2 hours.
Remove from pan.
Peel off wax paper.
Cut into squares.
Cover and store at room temperature.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and slice.
Dice green onions.
Add soup, melted butter, sour cream and cheese.
Place in casserole.
Mix corn flakes and butter.
Top casserole.
Bake covered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rocky road fudge brownies
directions: Prepare Brownie mix according to package directions. Stir in pecans, spoon batter into a greased 13 X 9 X 2 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle marshmallows over hot brownies.

title: frozen custard
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar thoroughly.
Stir in hot milk and cook in double boiler top, stirring occasionally until thickened. Beat egg yolks.
Stir in hot mixture gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook over simmering water, stirring occasionally until mixture coats a spoon.
Chill.
Fold into egg whites which have been beaten with salt until stiff.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla.
Pour into refrigerator tray and freeze until firm. Serves 6.

title: apple dumpling cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Spread apples and raisins evenly over bottom of pan.
In large bowl combine cake mix, 1/2 c. of water, margarine, sour cream and eggs at low speed until moistened. Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Spoon batter over fruit.
In small saucepan, heat 2 cups water and brown sugar to boiling.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40-50 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm inverted with a dollop of cream topping.
To warm:
cover pan with foil and heat at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix
pudding
and
milk and let set.
Fold in condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas.
Finish with pudding.
Sprinkle
top with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Keep refrigerated.
This makes a very large banana pudding.

title: chili sauce(makes 12 to 14 pints)
directions: Cook tomatoes.
Remove some water.
Add other vegetables and cook until tender, not mushy.
Put sauce into sterile hot jars one at a time.
Clean top of jar; put flat and ring on the jar and allow to cool.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients. Process until smooth.
Cover and chill.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: german lebkuchen(honey cookies)
directions: Sift together flour, soda and spices into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; blend thoroughly.
(Chill dough for easy handling.)
Roll out dough to about 1/8-inch thickness on board or canvas, sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Cut cookies in 1 x 2-inch strips.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: canadian wild goose
directions: Clean, singe, wash and dry the 6 to 7 pound goose.
Stuff with dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 500° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven to 350°.
Cover and bake 1 more hour.

title: honey vanilla ice cream(2 quarts)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add honey; beat at low speed until well blended.
Gradually blend in milk and vanilla.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Whip the cream until it forms soft peaks; fold into chilled mixture. Churn-freeze, using slightly greater portion salt to ice than for other ice creams.
After freezing, transfer ice cream to a plastic freezer container.
Ripen at least 3 hours before serving.

title: chicken supa
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips, lettuce, tomato and sour cream.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter until very soft.
Blend in sugar well.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Blend well.
Stir in, by hand, potato chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar when mostly cooled.
